45// MachineLoweringReducer, formerly known as EffectControlLinearizer, lowers
46// simplified operations to machine operations.
47template <typename Next>
48class MachineLoweringReducer : public Next {
49 public:
50 TURBOSHAFT_REDUCER_BOILERPLATE(MachineLowering)
51
52 bool NeedsHeapObjectCheck(ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions input_assumptions) {
53 // TODO(nicohartmann@): Consider type information once we have that.
54 switch (input_assumptions) {
55 case ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions::kNone:
56 return true;
57 case ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions::kHeapObject:
58 case ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions::kBigInt:
59 return false;
60 }
61 }
62
63 V<Word32> REDUCE(Word32SignHint)(V<Word32> input, Word32SignHintOp::Sign) {
64 // As far as Machine operations are concerned, Int32 and Uint32 are both
65 // Word32.
66 return input;
67 }
68
69 V<Untagged> REDUCE(ChangeOrDeopt)(V<Untagged> input,
70 V<FrameState> frame_state,
71 ChangeOrDeoptOp::Kind kind,
72 CheckForMinusZeroMode minus_zero_mode,
73 const FeedbackSource& feedback) {
74 switch (kind) {
75 case ChangeOrDeoptOp::Kind::kUint32ToInt32: {
76 __ DeoptimizeIf(__ Int32LessThan(V<Word32>::Cast(input), 0),
77 frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kLostPrecision,
78 feedback);
79 return input;
80 }
81 case ChangeOrDeoptOp::Kind::kInt64ToInt32: {
82 V<Word64> i64_input = V<Word64>::Cast(input);
83 V<Word32> i32 = __ TruncateWord64ToWord32(i64_input);
84 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(
85 __ Word64Equal(__ ChangeInt32ToInt64(i32), i64_input), frame_state,
86 DeoptimizeReason::kLostPrecision, feedback);
87 return i32;
88 }
89 case ChangeOrDeoptOp::Kind::kUint64ToInt32: {
90 V<Word64> i64_input = V<Word64>::Cast(input);
91 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(
92 __ Uint64LessThanOrEqual(i64_input, static_cast<uint64_t>(kMaxInt)),
93 frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kLostPrecision, feedback);
94 return __ TruncateWord64ToWord32(i64_input);
95 }
96 case ChangeOrDeoptOp::Kind::kUint64ToInt64: {
97 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(
98 __ Uint64LessThanOrEqual(V<Word64>::Cast(input),
99 std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::max()),
100 frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kLostPrecision, feedback);
101 return input;
102 }
103 case ChangeOrDeoptOp::Kind::kFloat64ToInt32: {
104 V<Float64> f64_input = V<Float64>::Cast(input);
105 V<Word32> i32 = __ TruncateFloat64ToInt32OverflowUndefined(f64_input);
106 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(
107 __ Float64Equal(__ ChangeInt32ToFloat64(i32), f64_input),
108 frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kLostPrecisionOrNaN, feedback);
109
110 if (minus_zero_mode == CheckForMinusZeroMode::kCheckForMinusZero) {
111 // Check if {value} is -0.
112 IF (UNLIKELY(__ Word32Equal(i32, 0))) {
113 // In case of 0, we need to check the high bits for the IEEE -0
114 // pattern.
115 V<Word32> check_negative =
116 __ Int32LessThan(__ Float64ExtractHighWord32(f64_input), 0);
117 __ DeoptimizeIf(check_negative, frame_state,
118 DeoptimizeReason::kMinusZero, feedback);
119 }
120 }
121
122 return i32;
123 }
124 case ChangeOrDeoptOp::Kind::kFloat64ToUint32: {
125 V<Float64> f64_input = V<Float64>::Cast(input);
126 V<Word32> ui32 = __ TruncateFloat64ToUint32OverflowUndefined(f64_input);
127 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(
128 __ Float64Equal(__ ChangeUint32ToFloat64(ui32), f64_input),
129 frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kLostPrecisionOrNaN, feedback);
130
131 if (minus_zero_mode == CheckForMinusZeroMode::kCheckForMinusZero) {
132 // Check if {value} is -0.
133 IF (UNLIKELY(__ Word32Equal(ui32, 0))) {
134 // In case of 0, we need to check the high bits for the IEEE -0
135 // pattern.
136 V<Word32> check_negative =
137 __ Int32LessThan(__ Float64ExtractHighWord32(f64_input), 0);
138 __ DeoptimizeIf(check_negative, frame_state,
139 DeoptimizeReason::kMinusZero, feedback);
140 }
141 }
142
143 return ui32;
144 }
145 case ChangeOrDeoptOp::Kind::kFloat64ToInt64: {
146 V<Float64> f64_input = V<Float64>::Cast(input);
147 V<Word64> i64 = __ TruncateFloat64ToInt64OverflowToMin(f64_input);
148 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(
149 __ Float64Equal(__ ChangeInt64ToFloat64(i64), f64_input),
150 frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kLostPrecisionOrNaN, feedback);
151
152 if (minus_zero_mode == CheckForMinusZeroMode::kCheckForMinusZero) {
153 // Check if {value} is -0.
154 IF (UNLIKELY(__ Word64Equal(i64, 0))) {
155 // In case of 0, we need to check the high bits for the IEEE -0
156 // pattern.
157 V<Word32> check_negative =
158 __ Int32LessThan(__ Float64ExtractHighWord32(f64_input), 0);
159 __ DeoptimizeIf(check_negative, frame_state,
160 DeoptimizeReason::kMinusZero, feedback);
161 }
162 }
163
164 return i64;
165 }
166 case ChangeOrDeoptOp::Kind::kFloat64NotHole: {
167 V<Float64> f64_input = V<Float64>::Cast(input);
168 // First check whether {value} is a NaN at all...
169 IF_NOT (LIKELY(__ Float64Equal(f64_input, f64_input))) {
170 // ...and only if {value} is a NaN, perform the expensive bit
171 // check. See http://crbug.com/v8/8264 for details.
172 __ DeoptimizeIf(__ Word32Equal(__ Float64ExtractHighWord32(f64_input),
173 kHoleNanUpper32),
174 frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kHole, feedback);
175 }
176
177 return input;
178 }
179 }
180 UNREACHABLE();
181 }
182
183 V<None> REDUCE(DeoptimizeIf)(V<Word32> condition, V<FrameState> frame_state,
184 bool negated,
185 const DeoptimizeParameters* parameters) {
186 LABEL_BLOCK(no_change) {
187 return Next::ReduceDeoptimizeIf(condition, frame_state, negated,
188 parameters);
189 }
190 if (ShouldSkipOptimizationStep()) goto no_change;
191 // Block cloning only works for branches, but not for `DeoptimizeIf`. On the
192 // other hand, explicit control flow makes the overall pipeline and
193 // especially the register allocator slower. So we only switch a
194 // `DeoptiomizeIf` to a branch if it has a phi input, which indicates that
195 // block cloning could be helpful.
196 if (__ Get(condition).template Is<PhiOp>()) {
197 if (negated) {
198 IF_NOT (LIKELY(condition)) {
199 __ Deoptimize(frame_state, parameters);
200 }
201
202 } else {
203 IF (UNLIKELY(condition)) {
204 __ Deoptimize(frame_state, parameters);
205 }
206 }
207 return V<None>::Invalid();
208 }
209 goto no_change;
210 }
211
212 V<Word32> REDUCE(ObjectIs)(V<Object> input, ObjectIsOp::Kind kind,
213 ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions input_assumptions) {
214 switch (kind) {
215 case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kBigInt:
216 case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kBigInt64: {
217 DCHECK_IMPLIES(kind == ObjectIsOp::Kind::kBigInt64, Is64());
218
219 Label<Word32> done(this);
220
221 if (input_assumptions != ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions::kBigInt) {
222 if (NeedsHeapObjectCheck(input_assumptions)) {
223 // Check for Smi.
224 GOTO_IF(__ IsSmi(input), done, 0);
225 }
226
227 // Check for BigInt.
228 V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(input);
229 V<Word32> is_bigint_map =
230 __ TaggedEqual(map, __ HeapConstant(factory_->bigint_map()));
231 GOTO_IF_NOT(is_bigint_map, done, 0);
232 }
233
234 if (kind == ObjectIsOp::Kind::kBigInt) {
235 GOTO(done, 1);
236 } else {
237 DCHECK_EQ(kind, ObjectIsOp::Kind::kBigInt64);
238 // We have to perform check for BigInt64 range.
239 V<Word32> bitfield = __ template LoadField<Word32>(
240 input, AccessBuilder::ForBigIntBitfield());
241 GOTO_IF(__ Word32Equal(bitfield, 0), done, 1);
242
243 // Length must be 1.
244 V<Word32> length_field =
245 __ Word32BitwiseAnd(bitfield, BigInt::LengthBits::kMask);
246 GOTO_IF_NOT(__ Word32Equal(length_field,
247 uint32_t{1} << BigInt::LengthBits::kShift),
248 done, 0);
249
250 // Check if it fits in 64 bit signed int.
251 V<Word64> lsd = __ template LoadField<Word64>(
252 input, AccessBuilder::ForBigIntLeastSignificantDigit64());
253 V<Word32> magnitude_check = __ Uint64LessThanOrEqual(
254 lsd, std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::max());
255 GOTO_IF(magnitude_check, done, 1);
256
257 // The BigInt probably doesn't fit into signed int64. The only
258 // exception is int64_t::min. We check for this.
259 V<Word32> sign =
260 __ Word32BitwiseAnd(bitfield, BigInt::SignBits::kMask);
261 V<Word32> sign_check = __ Word32Equal(sign, BigInt::SignBits::kMask);
262 GOTO_IF_NOT(sign_check, done, 0);
263
264 V<Word32> min_check =
265 __ Word64Equal(lsd, std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min());
266 GOTO_IF(min_check, done, 1);
267
268 GOTO(done, 0);
269 }
270
271 BIND(done, result);
272 return result;
273 }
274 case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kUndetectable:
275 if (DependOnNoUndetectableObjectsProtector()) {
276 V<Word32> is_undefined = __ TaggedEqual(
277 input, __ HeapConstant(factory_->undefined_value()));
278 V<Word32> is_null =
279 __ TaggedEqual(input, __ HeapConstant(factory_->null_value()));
280 return __ Word32BitwiseOr(is_undefined, is_null);
281 }
282 [[fallthrough]];
283 case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kCallable:
284 case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kConstructor:
285 case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kDetectableCallable:
286 case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kNonCallable:
287 case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kReceiver:
288 case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kReceiverOrNullOrUndefined: {
289 Label<Word32> done(this);
290
291 // Check for Smi if necessary.
292 if (NeedsHeapObjectCheck(input_assumptions)) {
293 GOTO_IF(UNLIKELY(__ IsSmi(input)), done, 0);
294 }
295
296#if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
297 // Fast check for NullOrUndefined before loading the map, if helpful.
298 V<Word32> is_null_or_undefined;
299 if (kind == ObjectIsOp::Kind::kReceiverOrNullOrUndefined) {
300 static_assert(StaticReadOnlyRoot::kFirstAllocatedRoot ==
301 StaticReadOnlyRoot::kUndefinedValue);
302 static_assert(StaticReadOnlyRoot::kUndefinedValue +
303 sizeof(Undefined) ==
304 StaticReadOnlyRoot::kNullValue);
305 is_null_or_undefined = __ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(
306 __ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(
307 __ BitcastHeapObjectToWordPtr(V<HeapObject>::Cast(input))),
308 __ Word32Constant(StaticReadOnlyRoot::kNullValue));
309 }
310#endif // V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
311
312 // Load bitfield from map.
313 V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(input);
314 V<Word32> bitfield =
315 __ template LoadField<Word32>(map, AccessBuilder::ForMapBitField());
316
317 V<Word32> check;
318 switch (kind) {
319 case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kCallable:
320 check =
321 __ Word32Equal(Map::Bits1::IsCallableBit::kMask,
322 __ Word32BitwiseAnd(
323 bitfield, Map::Bits1::IsCallableBit::kMask));
324 break;
325 case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kConstructor:
326 check = __ Word32Equal(
327 Map::Bits1::IsConstructorBit::kMask,
328 __ Word32BitwiseAnd(bitfield,
329 Map::Bits1::IsConstructorBit::kMask));
330 break;
331 case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kDetectableCallable:
332 check = __ Word32Equal(
333 Map::Bits1::IsCallableBit::kMask,
334 __ Word32BitwiseAnd(
335 bitfield, (Map::Bits1::IsCallableBit::kMask) |
336 (Map::Bits1::IsUndetectableBit::kMask)));
337 break;
338 case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kNonCallable:
339 check = __ Word32Equal(
340 0, __ Word32BitwiseAnd(bitfield,
341 Map::Bits1::IsCallableBit::kMask));
342 GOTO_IF_NOT(check, done, 0);
343 // Fallthrough into receiver check.
344 [[fallthrough]];
345 case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kReceiver:
346 check = JSAnyIsNotPrimitiveHeapObject(input, map);
347 break;
348 case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kReceiverOrNullOrUndefined: {
349#if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
350 V<Word32> is_non_primitive =
351 JSAnyIsNotPrimitiveHeapObject(input, map);
352 check = __ Word32BitwiseOr(is_null_or_undefined, is_non_primitive);
353#else
354 static_assert(LAST_PRIMITIVE_HEAP_OBJECT_TYPE == ODDBALL_TYPE);
355 static_assert(LAST_TYPE == LAST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE);
356 // Rule out all primitives except oddballs (true, false, undefined,
357 // null).
358 V<Word32> instance_type = __ LoadInstanceTypeField(map);
359 GOTO_IF_NOT(__ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(ODDBALL_TYPE, instance_type),
360 done, 0);
361
362 // Rule out booleans.
363 check = __ Word32Equal(
364 0,
365 __ TaggedEqual(map, __ HeapConstant(factory_->boolean_map())));
366#endif // V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
367 break;
368 }
369 case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kUndetectable:
370 check = __ Word32Equal(
371 Map::Bits1::IsUndetectableBit::kMask,
372 __ Word32BitwiseAnd(bitfield,
373 Map::Bits1::IsUndetectableBit::kMask));
374 break;
375 default:
376 UNREACHABLE();
377 }
378 GOTO(done, check);
379
380 BIND(done, result);
381 return result;
382 }
383 case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kSmi: {
384 // If we statically know that this is a heap object, it cannot be a Smi.
385 if (!NeedsHeapObjectCheck(input_assumptions)) {
386 return __ Word32Constant(0);
387 }
388 return __ IsSmi(input);
389 }
390 case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kNumber: {
391 Label<Word32> done(this);
392
393 // Check for Smi if necessary.
394 if (NeedsHeapObjectCheck(input_assumptions)) {
395 GOTO_IF(__ IsSmi(input), done, 1);
396 }
397
398 V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(input);
399 GOTO(done,
400 __ TaggedEqual(map, __ HeapConstant(factory_->heap_number_map())));
401
402 BIND(done, result);
403 return result;
404 }
405 case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kNumberFitsInt32: {
406 Label<Word32> done(this);
407
408 // Check for Smi if necessary.
409 if (NeedsHeapObjectCheck(input_assumptions)) {
410 GOTO_IF(__ IsSmi(input), done, 1);
411 }
412
413 V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(input);
414 GOTO_IF_NOT(
415 __ TaggedEqual(map, __ HeapConstant(factory_->heap_number_map())),
416 done, 0);
417
418 GOTO(done,
419 __ Float64Is(__ LoadHeapNumberValue(V<HeapNumber>::Cast(input)),
420 NumericKind::kInt32));
421
422 BIND(done, result);
423 return result;
424 }
425 case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kNumberOrBigInt: {
426 Label<Word32> done(this);
427 DCHECK_NE(input_assumptions, ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions::kBigInt);
428
429 // Check for Smi if necessary.
430 if (NeedsHeapObjectCheck(input_assumptions)) {
431 GOTO_IF(__ IsSmi(input), done, 1);
432 }
433
434 V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(input);
435 GOTO_IF(
436 __ TaggedEqual(map, __ HeapConstant(factory_->heap_number_map())),
437 done, 1);
438 GOTO(done,
439 __ TaggedEqual(map, __ HeapConstant(factory_->bigint_map())));
440
441 BIND(done, result);
442 return result;
443 }
444
445#if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
446 case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kString: {
447 Label<Word32> done(this);
448
449 // Check for Smi if necessary.
450 if (NeedsHeapObjectCheck(input_assumptions)) {
451 GOTO_IF(__ IsSmi(input), done, 0);
452 }
453
454 V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(input);
455 GOTO(done,
456 __ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(
457 __ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(__ BitcastHeapObjectToWordPtr(map)),
458 __ Word32Constant(InstanceTypeChecker::kStringMapUpperBound)));
459
460 BIND(done, result);
461 return result;
462 }
463 case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kSymbol: {
464 Label<Word32> done(this);
465
466 // Check for Smi if necessary.
467 if (NeedsHeapObjectCheck(input_assumptions)) {
468 GOTO_IF(__ IsSmi(input), done, 0);
469 }
470
471 V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(input);
472 GOTO(done,
473 __ Word32Equal(
474 __ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(__ BitcastHeapObjectToWordPtr(map)),
475 __ Word32Constant(StaticReadOnlyRoot::kSymbolMap)));
476
477 BIND(done, result);
478 return result;
479 }
480#else
481 case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kString:
482 case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kSymbol:
483#endif
484 case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kArrayBufferView: {
485 Label<Word32> done(this);
486
487 // Check for Smi if necessary.
488 if (NeedsHeapObjectCheck(input_assumptions)) {
489 GOTO_IF(__ IsSmi(input), done, 0);
490 }
491
492 // Load instance type from map.
493 V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(input);
494 V<Word32> instance_type = __ LoadInstanceTypeField(map);
495
496 V<Word32> check;
497 switch (kind) {
498#if !V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
499 case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kSymbol:
500 check = __ Word32Equal(instance_type, SYMBOL_TYPE);
501 break;
502 case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kString:
503 check = __ Uint32LessThan(instance_type, FIRST_NONSTRING_TYPE);
504 break;
505#endif
506 case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kArrayBufferView:
507 check = __ Uint32LessThan(
508 __ Word32Sub(instance_type, FIRST_JS_ARRAY_BUFFER_VIEW_TYPE),
509 LAST_JS_ARRAY_BUFFER_VIEW_TYPE -
510 FIRST_JS_ARRAY_BUFFER_VIEW_TYPE + 1);
511 break;
512 default:
513 UNREACHABLE();
514 }
515 GOTO(done, check);
516
517 BIND(done, result);
518 return result;
519 }
520 case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kInternalizedString: {
521 DCHECK_EQ(input_assumptions, ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions::kHeapObject);
522 // Load instance type from map.
523 V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(input);
524 V<Word32> instance_type = __ LoadInstanceTypeField(map);
525
526 return __ Word32Equal(
527 __ Word32BitwiseAnd(instance_type,
528 (kIsNotStringMask | kIsNotInternalizedMask)),
529 kInternalizedTag);
530 }
531 case ObjectIsOp::Kind::kStringOrStringWrapper: {
532 Label<Word32> done(this);
533
534 // Check for Smi if necessary.
535 if (NeedsHeapObjectCheck(input_assumptions)) {
536 GOTO_IF(__ IsSmi(input), done, 0);
537 }
538
539 // Load instance type from map.
540 V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(input);
541 V<Word32> instance_type = __ LoadInstanceTypeField(map);
542
543 GOTO_IF(__ Uint32LessThan(instance_type, FIRST_NONSTRING_TYPE), done,
544 1);
545 GOTO_IF_NOT(__ Word32Equal(instance_type, JS_PRIMITIVE_WRAPPER_TYPE),
546 done, 0);
547
548 V<Word32> bitfield2 = __ template LoadField<Word32>(
549 map, AccessBuilder::ForMapBitField2());
550
551 V<Word32> elements_kind =
552 __ Word32BitwiseAnd(bitfield2, Map::Bits2::ElementsKindBits::kMask);
553
554 GOTO_IF(__ Word32Equal(FAST_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS
555 << Map::Bits2::ElementsKindBits::kShift,
556 elements_kind),
557 done, 1);
558
559 V<Word32> check =
560 __ Word32Equal(SLOW_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS
561 << Map::Bits2::ElementsKindBits::kShift,
562 elements_kind);
563 GOTO(done, check);
564
565 BIND(done, result);
566 return result;
567 }
568 }
569 UNREACHABLE();
570 }
571
572 V<Word32> REDUCE(Float64Is)(V<Float64> value, NumericKind kind) {
573 switch (kind) {
574 case NumericKind::kFloat64Hole: {
575 Label<Word32> done(this);
576 // First check whether {value} is a NaN at all...
577 GOTO_IF(LIKELY(__ Float64Equal(value, value)), done, 0);
578 // ...and only if {value} is a NaN, perform the expensive bit
579 // check. See http://crbug.com/v8/8264 for details.
580 GOTO(done, __ Word32Equal(__ Float64ExtractHighWord32(value),
581 kHoleNanUpper32));
582 BIND(done, result);
583 return result;
584 }
585 case NumericKind::kFinite: {
586 V<Float64> diff = __ Float64Sub(value, value);
587 return __ Float64Equal(diff, diff);
588 }
589 case NumericKind::kInteger: {
590 V<Float64> trunc = __ Float64RoundToZero(value);
591 V<Float64> diff = __ Float64Sub(value, trunc);
592 return __ Float64Equal(diff, 0.0);
593 }
594 case NumericKind::kSafeInteger: {
595 Label<Word32> done(this);
596 V<Float64> trunc = __ Float64RoundToZero(value);
597 V<Float64> diff = __ Float64Sub(value, trunc);
598 GOTO_IF_NOT(__ Float64Equal(diff, 0), done, 0);
599 V<Word32> in_range =
600 __ Float64LessThanOrEqual(__ Float64Abs(trunc), kMaxSafeInteger);
601 GOTO(done, in_range);
602
603 BIND(done, result);
604 return result;
605 }
606 case NumericKind::kInt32: {
607 Label<Word32> done(this);
608 V<Word32> v32 = __ TruncateFloat64ToInt32OverflowUndefined(value);
609 GOTO_IF_NOT(__ Float64Equal(value, __ ChangeInt32ToFloat64(v32)), done,
610 0);
611 IF (__ Word32Equal(v32, 0)) {
612 // Checking -0.
613 GOTO_IF(__ Int32LessThan(__ Float64ExtractHighWord32(value), 0), done,
614 0);
615 }
616 GOTO(done, 1);
617
618 BIND(done, result);
619 return result;
620 }
621 case NumericKind::kSmi: {
622 Label<Word32> done(this);
623 V<Word32> v32 = __ TruncateFloat64ToInt32OverflowUndefined(value);
624 GOTO_IF_NOT(__ Float64Equal(value, __ ChangeInt32ToFloat64(v32)), done,
625 0);
626 IF (__ Word32Equal(v32, 0)) {
627 // Checking -0.
628 GOTO_IF(__ Int32LessThan(__ Float64ExtractHighWord32(value), 0), done,
629 0);
630 }
631
632 if constexpr (SmiValuesAre32Bits()) {
633 GOTO(done, 1);
634 } else {
635 V<Tuple<Word32, Word32>> add = __ Int32AddCheckOverflow(v32, v32);
636 V<Word32> overflow = __ template Projection<1>(add);
637 GOTO_IF(overflow, done, 0);
638 GOTO(done, 1);
639 }
640
641 BIND(done, result);
642 return result;
643 }
644 case NumericKind::kMinusZero: {
645 if (Is64()) {
646 V<Word64> value64 = __ BitcastFloat64ToWord64(value);
647 return __ Word64Equal(value64, kMinusZeroBits);
648 } else {
649 Label<Word32> done(this);
650 V<Word32> value_lo = __ Float64ExtractLowWord32(value);
651 GOTO_IF_NOT(__ Word32Equal(value_lo, kMinusZeroLoBits), done, 0);
652 V<Word32> value_hi = __ Float64ExtractHighWord32(value);
653 GOTO(done, __ Word32Equal(value_hi, kMinusZeroHiBits));
654
655 BIND(done, result);
656 return result;
657 }
658 }
659 case NumericKind::kNaN: {
660 V<Word32> diff = __ Float64Equal(value, value);
661 return __ Word32Equal(diff, 0);
662 }
663 }
664
665 UNREACHABLE();
666 }
667
668 V<Word32> REDUCE(ObjectIsNumericValue)(V<Object> input, NumericKind kind,
669 FloatRepresentation input_rep) {
670 DCHECK_EQ(input_rep, FloatRepresentation::Float64());
671 Label<Word32> done(this);
672
673 switch (kind) {
674 case NumericKind::kFinite:
675 case NumericKind::kInteger:
676 case NumericKind::kSafeInteger:
677 case NumericKind::kInt32:
678 case NumericKind::kSmi:
679 GOTO_IF(__ IsSmi(input), done, 1);
680 break;
681 case NumericKind::kMinusZero:
682 case NumericKind::kNaN:
683 GOTO_IF(__ IsSmi(input), done, 0);
684 break;
685 case NumericKind::kFloat64Hole:
686 // ObjectIsFloat64Hole is not used, but can be implemented when needed.
687 UNREACHABLE();
688 }
689
690 V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(input);
691 GOTO_IF_NOT(
692 __ TaggedEqual(map, __ HeapConstant(factory_->heap_number_map())), done,
693 0);
694
695 V<Float64> value = __ LoadHeapNumberValue(V<HeapNumber>::Cast(input));
696 GOTO(done, __ Float64Is(value, kind));
697
698 BIND(done, result);
699 return result;
700 }
701
702 V<Object> REDUCE(Convert)(V<Object> input, ConvertOp::Kind from,
703 ConvertOp::Kind to) {
704 switch (to) {
705 case ConvertOp::Kind::kNumber: {
706 if (from == ConvertOp::Kind::kPlainPrimitive) {
707 return __ CallBuiltin_PlainPrimitiveToNumber(
708 isolate_, V<PlainPrimitive>::Cast(input));
709 } else {
710 DCHECK_EQ(from, ConvertOp::Kind::kString);
711 return __ CallBuiltin_StringToNumber(isolate_,
712 V<String>::Cast(input));
713 }
714 }
715 case ConvertOp::Kind::kBoolean: {
716 DCHECK_EQ(from, ConvertOp::Kind::kObject);
717 return __ CallBuiltin_ToBoolean(isolate_, input);
718 }
719 case ConvertOp::Kind::kString: {
720 DCHECK_EQ(from, ConvertOp::Kind::kNumber);
721 return __ CallBuiltin_NumberToString(isolate_, V<Number>::Cast(input));
722 }
723 case ConvertOp::Kind::kSmi: {
724 DCHECK_EQ(from, ConvertOp::Kind::kNumberOrOddball);
725 Label<Smi> done(this);
726 GOTO_IF(LIKELY(__ ObjectIsSmi(input)), done, V<Smi>::Cast(input));
727
728 V<Float64> value = __ template LoadField<Float64>(
729 input, AccessBuilder::ForHeapNumberOrOddballOrHoleValue());
730 GOTO(done, __ TagSmi(__ ReversibleFloat64ToInt32(value)));
731
732 BIND(done, result);
733 return result;
734 }
735 default:
736 UNREACHABLE();
737 }
738 }
739
740 V<JSPrimitive> REDUCE(ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitive)(
741 V<Untagged> input, ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::JSPrimitiveKind kind,
742 RegisterRepresentation input_rep,
743 ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation input_interpretation,
744 CheckForMinusZeroMode minus_zero_mode) {
745 switch (kind) {
746 case ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kBigInt: {
747 DCHECK(Is64());
748 DCHECK_EQ(input_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Word64());
749 V<Word64> input_w64 = V<Word64>::Cast(input);
750 Label<BigInt> done(this);
751
752 // BigInts with value 0 must be of size 0 (canonical form).
753 GOTO_IF(__ Word64Equal(input_w64, int64_t{0}), done,
754 AllocateBigInt(V<Word32>::Invalid(), V<Word64>::Invalid()));
755
756 // The GOTO_IF above could have been changed to an unconditional GOTO,
757 // in which case we are now in unreachable code, so we can skip the
758 // following step and return.
759 if (input_interpretation ==
760 ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::kSigned) {
761 // Shift sign bit into BigInt's sign bit position.
762 V<Word32> bitfield = __ Word32BitwiseOr(
763 BigInt::LengthBits::encode(1),
764 __ TruncateWord64ToWord32(__ Word64ShiftRightLogical(
765 input_w64,
766 static_cast<int32_t>(63 - BigInt::SignBits::kShift))));
767
768 // We use (value XOR (value >> 63)) - (value >> 63) to compute the
769 // absolute value, in a branchless fashion.
770 V<Word64> sign_mask =
771 __ Word64ShiftRightArithmetic(input_w64, int32_t{63});
772 V<Word64> absolute_value = __ Word64Sub(
773 __ Word64BitwiseXor(input_w64, sign_mask), sign_mask);
774 GOTO(done, AllocateBigInt(bitfield, absolute_value));
775 } else {
776 DCHECK_EQ(
777 input_interpretation,
778 ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::kUnsigned);
779 const auto bitfield = BigInt::LengthBits::encode(1);
780 GOTO(done, AllocateBigInt(__ Word32Constant(bitfield), input_w64));
781 }
782
783 BIND(done, result);
784 return result;
785 }
786 case ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kNumber: {
787 if (input_rep == RegisterRepresentation::Word32()) {
788 V<Word32> input_w32 = V<Word32>::Cast(input);
789 switch (input_interpretation) {
790 case ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::kSigned: {
791 if (SmiValuesAre32Bits()) {
792 return __ TagSmi(input_w32);
793 }
794 DCHECK(SmiValuesAre31Bits());
795
796 Label<Number> done(this);
797 Label<> overflow(this);
798
799 TagSmiOrOverflow(input_w32, &overflow, &done);
800
801 if (BIND(overflow)) {
802 GOTO(done,
803 AllocateHeapNumber(__ ChangeInt32ToFloat64(input_w32)));
804 }
805
806 BIND(done, result);
807 return result;
808 }
809 case ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::
810 kUnsigned: {
811 Label<Number> done(this);
812
813 GOTO_IF(__ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(input_w32, Smi::kMaxValue), done,
814 __ TagSmi(input_w32));
815 GOTO(done,
816 AllocateHeapNumber(__ ChangeUint32ToFloat64(input_w32)));
817
818 BIND(done, result);
819 return result;
820 }
821 case ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::kCharCode:
822 case ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::
823 kCodePoint:
824 UNREACHABLE();
825 }
826 } else if (input_rep == RegisterRepresentation::Word64()) {
827 V<Word64> input_w64 = V<Word64>::Cast(input);
828 switch (input_interpretation) {
829 case ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::kSigned: {
830 Label<Number> done(this);
831 Label<> outside_smi_range(this);
832
833 V<Word32> v32 = __ TruncateWord64ToWord32(input_w64);
834 V<Word64> v64 = __ ChangeInt32ToInt64(v32);
835 GOTO_IF_NOT(__ Word64Equal(v64, input_w64), outside_smi_range);
836
837 if constexpr (SmiValuesAre32Bits()) {
838 GOTO(done, __ TagSmi(v32));
839 } else {
840 TagSmiOrOverflow(v32, &outside_smi_range, &done);
841 }
842
843 if (BIND(outside_smi_range)) {
844 GOTO(done,
845 AllocateHeapNumber(__ ChangeInt64ToFloat64(input_w64)));
846 }
847
848 BIND(done, result);
849 return result;
850 }
851 case ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::
852 kUnsigned: {
853 Label<Number> done(this);
854
855 GOTO_IF(__ Uint64LessThanOrEqual(input_w64, Smi::kMaxValue), done,
856 __ TagSmi(__ TruncateWord64ToWord32(input_w64)));
857 GOTO(done,
858 AllocateHeapNumber(__ ChangeInt64ToFloat64(input_w64)));
859
860 BIND(done, result);
861 return result;
862 }
863 case ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::kCharCode:
864 case ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::
865 kCodePoint:
866 UNREACHABLE();
867 }
868 } else {
869 DCHECK_EQ(input_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Float64());
870 V<Float64> input_f64 = V<Float64>::Cast(input);
871 Label<Number> done(this);
872 Label<> outside_smi_range(this);
873
874 V<Word32> v32 = __ TruncateFloat64ToInt32OverflowUndefined(input_f64);
875 GOTO_IF_NOT(__ Float64Equal(input_f64, __ ChangeInt32ToFloat64(v32)),
876 outside_smi_range);
877
878 if (minus_zero_mode == CheckForMinusZeroMode::kCheckForMinusZero) {
879 // In case of 0, we need to check the high bits for the IEEE -0
880 // pattern.
881 IF (__ Word32Equal(v32, 0)) {
882 GOTO_IF(
883 __ Int32LessThan(__ Float64ExtractHighWord32(input_f64), 0),
884 outside_smi_range);
885 }
886 }
887
888 if constexpr (SmiValuesAre32Bits()) {
889 GOTO(done, __ TagSmi(v32));
890 } else {
891 TagSmiOrOverflow(v32, &outside_smi_range, &done);
892 }
893
894 if (BIND(outside_smi_range)) {
895 GOTO(done, AllocateHeapNumber(input_f64));
896 }
897
898 BIND(done, result);
899 return result;
900 }
901 UNREACHABLE();
902 break;
903 }
904 case ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kHeapNumber: {
905 DCHECK_EQ(input_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Float64());
906 DCHECK_EQ(input_interpretation,
907 ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::kSigned);
908 return AllocateHeapNumber(V<Float64>::Cast(input));
909 }
910 case ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::JSPrimitiveKind::
911 kHeapNumberOrUndefined: {
912 DCHECK_EQ(input_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Float64());
913 V<Float64> input_f64 = V<Float64>::Cast(input);
914 DCHECK_EQ(input_interpretation,
915 ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::kSigned);
916 Label<Union<HeapNumber, Undefined>> done(this);
917 Label<> allocate_heap_number(this);
918
919 // First check whether {input} is a NaN at all...
920 IF (UNLIKELY(__ Float64IsNaN(input_f64))) {
921 // ...and only if {input} is a NaN, perform the expensive signaling
922 // NaN bit check. See http://crbug.com/v8/8264 for details.
923 GOTO_IF_NOT(__ Word32Equal(__ Float64ExtractHighWord32(input_f64),
924 kHoleNanUpper32),
925 allocate_heap_number);
926 GOTO(done, __ HeapConstant(factory_->undefined_value()));
927 } ELSE {
928 GOTO(allocate_heap_number);
929 }
930
931 if (BIND(allocate_heap_number)) {
932 GOTO(done, AllocateHeapNumber(input_f64));
933 }
934
935 BIND(done, result);
936 return result;
937 }
938 case ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kSmi: {
939 DCHECK_EQ(input_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Word32());
940 DCHECK_EQ(input_interpretation,
941 ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::kSigned);
942 return __ TagSmi(V<Word32>::Cast(input));
943 }
944 case ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kBoolean: {
945 DCHECK_EQ(input_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Word32());
946 DCHECK_EQ(input_interpretation,
947 ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::kSigned);
948 Label<Boolean> done(this);
949
950 IF (V<Word32>::Cast(input)) {
951 GOTO(done, __ HeapConstant(factory_->true_value()));
952 } ELSE {
953 GOTO(done, __ HeapConstant(factory_->false_value()));
954 }
955
956 BIND(done, result);
957 return result;
958 }
959 case ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kString: {
960 DCHECK_EQ(input_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Word32());
961 V<Word32> input_w32 = V<Word32>::Cast(input);
962
963 switch (input_interpretation) {
964 case ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::kCharCode:
965 return StringFromSingleCharCode(
966 __ Word32BitwiseAnd(input_w32, 0xFFFF));
967 case ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::
968 kCodePoint: {
969 return StringFromSingleCodePoint(input_w32, UnicodeEncoding::UTF32);
970 }
971 default:
972 UNREACHABLE();
973 }
974 }
975 }
976
977 UNREACHABLE();
978 }
979
980 V<JSPrimitive> REDUCE(ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOrDeopt)(
981 V<Untagged> input, V<FrameState> frame_state,
982 ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOrDeoptOp::JSPrimitiveKind kind,
983 RegisterRepresentation input_rep,
984 ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOrDeoptOp::InputInterpretation
985 input_interpretation,
986 const FeedbackSource& feedback) {
987 DCHECK_EQ(kind,
988 ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOrDeoptOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kSmi);
989 if (input_rep == RegisterRepresentation::Word32()) {
990 V<Word32> input_w32 = V<Word32>::Cast(input);
991 if (input_interpretation ==
992 ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOrDeoptOp::InputInterpretation::kSigned) {
993 if constexpr (SmiValuesAre32Bits()) {
994 return __ TagSmi(input_w32);
995 } else {
996 V<Tuple<Word32, Word32>> test =
997 __ Int32AddCheckOverflow(input_w32, input_w32);
998 __ DeoptimizeIf(__ template Projection<1>(test), frame_state,
999 DeoptimizeReason::kLostPrecision, feedback);
1000 return __ BitcastWord32ToSmi(__ template Projection<0>(test));
1001 }
1002 } else {
1003 DCHECK_EQ(input_interpretation, ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOrDeoptOp::
1004 InputInterpretation::kUnsigned);
1005 V<Word32> check = __ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(input_w32, Smi::kMaxValue);
1006 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(check, frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kLostPrecision,
1007 feedback);
1008 return __ TagSmi(input_w32);
1009 }
1010 } else {
1011 DCHECK_EQ(input_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Word64());
1012 V<Word64> input_w64 = V<Word64>::Cast(input);
1013 if (input_interpretation ==
1014 ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOrDeoptOp::InputInterpretation::kSigned) {
1015 V<Word32> i32 = __ TruncateWord64ToWord32(input_w64);
1016 V<Word32> check = __ Word64Equal(__ ChangeInt32ToInt64(i32), input_w64);
1017 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(check, frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kLostPrecision,
1018 feedback);
1019 if constexpr (SmiValuesAre32Bits()) {
1020 return __ TagSmi(i32);
1021 } else {
1022 V<Tuple<Word32, Word32>> test = __ Int32AddCheckOverflow(i32, i32);
1023 __ DeoptimizeIf(__ template Projection<1>(test), frame_state,
1024 DeoptimizeReason::kLostPrecision, feedback);
1025 return __ BitcastWord32ToSmi(__ template Projection<0>(test));
1026 }
1027 } else {
1028 DCHECK_EQ(input_interpretation, ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOrDeoptOp::
1029 InputInterpretation::kUnsigned);
1030 V<Word32> check = __ Uint64LessThanOrEqual(
1031 input_w64, static_cast<uint64_t>(Smi::kMaxValue));
1032 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(check, frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kLostPrecision,
1033 feedback);
1034 return __ TagSmi(__ TruncateWord64ToWord32(input_w64));
1035 }
1036 }
1037
1038 UNREACHABLE();
1039 }
1040
1041 V<Untagged> REDUCE(ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntagged)(
1042 V<JSPrimitive> object, ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::UntaggedKind kind,
1043 ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::InputAssumptions input_assumptions) {
1044 switch (kind) {
1045 case ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::UntaggedKind::kInt32:
1046 if (input_assumptions ==
1047 ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::InputAssumptions::kSmi) {
1048 return __ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(object));
1049 } else if (input_assumptions ==
1050 ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::InputAssumptions::
1051 kNumberOrOddball) {
1052 Label<Word32> done(this);
1053
1054 IF (LIKELY(__ ObjectIsSmi(object))) {
1055 GOTO(done, __ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(object)));
1056 } ELSE {
1057 V<Float64> value = __ template LoadField<Float64>(
1058 object, AccessBuilder::ForHeapNumberOrOddballOrHoleValue());
1059 GOTO(done, __ ReversibleFloat64ToInt32(value));
1060 }
1061
1062 BIND(done, result);
1063 return result;
1064 } else {
1065 DCHECK_EQ(input_assumptions, ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::
1066 InputAssumptions::kPlainPrimitive);
1067 Label<Word32> done(this);
1068 GOTO_IF(LIKELY(__ ObjectIsSmi(object)), done,
1069 __ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(object)));
1070 V<Number> number =
1071 __ ConvertPlainPrimitiveToNumber(V<PlainPrimitive>::Cast(object));
1072 GOTO_IF(__ ObjectIsSmi(number), done,
1073 __ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(number)));
1074 V<Float64> f64 = __ LoadHeapNumberValue(V<HeapNumber>::Cast(number));
1075 GOTO(done, __ JSTruncateFloat64ToWord32(f64));
1076 BIND(done, result);
1077 return result;
1078 }
1079 UNREACHABLE();
1080 case ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::UntaggedKind::kInt64:
1081 if (input_assumptions ==
1082 ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::InputAssumptions::kSmi) {
1083 return __ ChangeInt32ToInt64(__ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(object)));
1084 } else {
1085 DCHECK_EQ(input_assumptions, ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::
1086 InputAssumptions::kNumberOrOddball);
1087 Label<Word64> done(this);
1088
1089 IF (LIKELY(__ ObjectIsSmi(object))) {
1090 GOTO(done,
1091 __ ChangeInt32ToInt64(__ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(object))));
1092 } ELSE {
1093 V<Float64> value = __ template LoadField<Float64>(
1094 object, AccessBuilder::ForHeapNumberOrOddballOrHoleValue());
1095 GOTO(done, __ ReversibleFloat64ToInt64(value));
1096 }
1097
1098 BIND(done, result);
1099 return result;
1100 }
1101 UNREACHABLE();
1102 case ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::UntaggedKind::kUint32: {
1103 DCHECK_EQ(
1104 input_assumptions,
1105 ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::InputAssumptions::kNumberOrOddball);
1106 Label<Word32> done(this);
1107
1108 IF (LIKELY(__ ObjectIsSmi(object))) {
1109 GOTO(done, __ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(object)));
1110 } ELSE {
1111 V<Float64> value = __ template LoadField<Float64>(
1112 object, AccessBuilder::ForHeapNumberOrOddballOrHoleValue());
1113 GOTO(done, __ ReversibleFloat64ToUint32(value));
1114 }
1115
1116 BIND(done, result);
1117 return result;
1118 }
1119 case ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::UntaggedKind::kBit:
1120 DCHECK_EQ(input_assumptions,
1121 ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::InputAssumptions::kBoolean);
1122 return __ TaggedEqual(object, __ HeapConstant(factory_->true_value()));
1123 case ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::UntaggedKind::kFloat64: {
1124 if (input_assumptions == ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::
1125 InputAssumptions::kNumberOrOddball) {
1126 Label<Float64> done(this);
1127
1128 IF (LIKELY(__ ObjectIsSmi(object))) {
1129 GOTO(done,
1130 __ ChangeInt32ToFloat64(__ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(object))));
1131 } ELSE {
1132 V<Float64> value = __ template LoadField<Float64>(
1133 object, AccessBuilder::ForHeapNumberOrOddballOrHoleValue());
1134 GOTO(done, value);
1135 }
1136
1137 BIND(done, result);
1138 return result;
1139 } else {
1140 DCHECK_EQ(input_assumptions, ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::
1141 InputAssumptions::kPlainPrimitive);
1142 Label<Float64> done(this);
1143 GOTO_IF(LIKELY(__ ObjectIsSmi(object)), done,
1144 __ ChangeInt32ToFloat64(__ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(object))));
1145 V<Number> number =
1146 __ ConvertPlainPrimitiveToNumber(V<PlainPrimitive>::Cast(object));
1147 GOTO_IF(__ ObjectIsSmi(number), done,
1148 __ ChangeInt32ToFloat64(__ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(number))));
1149 V<Float64> f64 = __ LoadHeapNumberValue(V<HeapNumber>::Cast(number));
1150 GOTO(done, f64);
1151 BIND(done, result);
1152 return result;
1153 }
1154 }
1155 }
1156 UNREACHABLE();
1157 }
1158
1159 V<Untagged> REDUCE(ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeopt)(
1160 V<Object> object, V<FrameState> frame_state,
1161 ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::JSPrimitiveKind from_kind,
1162 ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::UntaggedKind to_kind,
1163 CheckForMinusZeroMode minus_zero_mode, const FeedbackSource& feedback) {
1164 switch (to_kind) {
1165 case ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::UntaggedKind::kInt32: {
1166 if (from_kind ==
1167 ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kSmi) {
1168 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(__ ObjectIsSmi(object), frame_state,
1169 DeoptimizeReason::kNotASmi, feedback);
1170 return __ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(object));
1171 } else {
1172 DCHECK_EQ(
1173 from_kind,
1174 ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kNumber);
1175 Label<Word32> done(this);
1176
1177 IF (LIKELY(__ ObjectIsSmi(object))) {
1178 GOTO(done, __ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(object)));
1179 } ELSE {
1180 V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(object);
1181 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(
1182 __ TaggedEqual(map,
1183 __ HeapConstant(factory_->heap_number_map())),
1184 frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kNotAHeapNumber, feedback);
1185 V<Float64> heap_number_value =
1186 __ LoadHeapNumberValue(V<HeapNumber>::Cast(object));
1187
1188 GOTO(done,
1189 __ ChangeFloat64ToInt32OrDeopt(heap_number_value, frame_state,
1190 minus_zero_mode, feedback));
1191 }
1192
1193 BIND(done, result);
1194 return result;
1195 }
1196 }
1197 case ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::UntaggedKind::kInt64: {
1198 DCHECK_EQ(
1199 from_kind,
1200 ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kNumber);
1201 Label<Word64> done(this);
1202
1203 IF (LIKELY(__ ObjectIsSmi(object))) {
1204 GOTO(done, __ ChangeInt32ToInt64(__ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(object))));
1205 } ELSE {
1206 V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(object);
1207 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(
1208 __ TaggedEqual(map, __ HeapConstant(factory_->heap_number_map())),
1209 frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kNotAHeapNumber, feedback);
1210 V<Float64> heap_number_value =
1211 __ LoadHeapNumberValue(V<HeapNumber>::Cast(object));
1212 GOTO(done,
1213 __ ChangeFloat64ToInt64OrDeopt(heap_number_value, frame_state,
1214 minus_zero_mode, feedback));
1215 }
1216
1217 BIND(done, result);
1218 return result;
1219 }
1220 case ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::UntaggedKind::kFloat64: {
1221 Label<Float64> done(this);
1222
1223 // In the Smi case, just convert to int32 and then float64.
1224 // Otherwise, check heap numberness and load the number.
1225 IF (__ ObjectIsSmi(object)) {
1226 GOTO(done,
1227 __ ChangeInt32ToFloat64(__ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(object))));
1228 } ELSE {
1229 GOTO(done, ConvertHeapObjectToFloat64OrDeopt(object, frame_state,
1230 from_kind, feedback));
1231 }
1232
1233 BIND(done, result);
1234 return result;
1235 }
1236 case ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::UntaggedKind::kArrayIndex: {
1237 DCHECK_EQ(from_kind, ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::
1238 JSPrimitiveKind::kNumberOrString);
1239 Label<WordPtr> done(this);
1240
1241 IF (LIKELY(__ ObjectIsSmi(object))) {
1242 // In the Smi case, just convert to intptr_t.
1243 GOTO(done, __ ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(__ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(object))));
1244 } ELSE {
1245 V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(object);
1246 IF (LIKELY(__ TaggedEqual(
1247 map, __ HeapConstant(factory_->heap_number_map())))) {
1248 V<Float64> heap_number_value =
1249 __ LoadHeapNumberValue(V<HeapNumber>::Cast(object));
1250 // Perform Turbofan's "CheckedFloat64ToIndex"
1251 {
1252 if constexpr (Is64()) {
1253 V<Word64> i64 = __ TruncateFloat64ToInt64OverflowUndefined(
1254 heap_number_value);
1255 // The TruncateKind above means there will be a precision loss
1256 // in case INT64_MAX input is passed, but that precision loss
1257 // would not be detected and would not lead to a deoptimization
1258 // from the first check. But in this case, we'll deopt anyway
1259 // because of the following checks.
1260 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(__ Float64Equal(__ ChangeInt64ToFloat64(i64),
1261 heap_number_value),
1262 frame_state,
1263 DeoptimizeReason::kLostPrecisionOrNaN,
1264 feedback);
1265 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(
1266 __ IntPtrLessThan(i64, kMaxSafeIntegerUint64), frame_state,
1267 DeoptimizeReason::kNotAnArrayIndex, feedback);
1268 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(
1269 __ IntPtrLessThan(-kMaxSafeIntegerUint64, i64), frame_state,
1270 DeoptimizeReason::kNotAnArrayIndex, feedback);
1271 GOTO(done, i64);
1272 } else {
1273 V<Word32> i32 = __ TruncateFloat64ToInt32OverflowUndefined(
1274 heap_number_value);
1275 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(__ Float64Equal(__ ChangeInt32ToFloat64(i32),
1276 heap_number_value),
1277 frame_state,
1278 DeoptimizeReason::kLostPrecisionOrNaN,
1279 feedback);
1280 GOTO(done, i32);
1281 }
1282 }
1283 } ELSE {
1284#if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
1285 V<Word32> is_string_map = __ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(
1286 __ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(__ BitcastHeapObjectToWordPtr(map)),
1287 __ Word32Constant(InstanceTypeChecker::kStringMapUpperBound));
1288#else
1289 V<Word32> instance_type = __ LoadInstanceTypeField(map);
1290 V<Word32> is_string_map =
1291 __ Uint32LessThan(instance_type, FIRST_NONSTRING_TYPE);
1292#endif
1293 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(is_string_map, frame_state,
1294 DeoptimizeReason::kNotAString, feedback);
1295
1296 // TODO(nicohartmann@): We might introduce a Turboshaft way for
1297 // constructing call descriptors.
1298 MachineSignature::Builder builder(__ graph_zone(), 1, 1);
1299 builder.AddReturn(MachineType::Int32());
1300 builder.AddParam(MachineType::TaggedPointer());
1301 auto desc = Linkage::GetSimplifiedCDescriptor(__ graph_zone(),
1302 builder.Get());
1303 auto ts_desc = TSCallDescriptor::Create(
1304 desc, CanThrow::kNo, LazyDeoptOnThrow::kNo, __ graph_zone());
1305 OpIndex callee = __ ExternalConstant(
1306 ExternalReference::string_to_array_index_function());
1307 // NOTE: String::ToArrayIndex() currently returns int32_t.
1308 V<WordPtr> index = __ ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(
1309 V<Word32>::Cast(__ Call(callee, {object}, ts_desc)));
1310 __ DeoptimizeIf(__ WordPtrEqual(index, -1), frame_state,
1311 DeoptimizeReason::kNotAnArrayIndex, feedback);
1312 GOTO(done, index);
1313 }
1314 }
1315
1316 BIND(done, result);
1317 return result;
1318 }
1319 }
1320 UNREACHABLE();
1321 }
1322
1323 V<Word> REDUCE(TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntagged)(
1324 V<JSPrimitive> object, TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::UntaggedKind kind,
1325 TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::InputAssumptions input_assumptions) {
1326 switch (kind) {
1327 case TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::UntaggedKind::kInt32: {
1328 DCHECK_EQ(input_assumptions, TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::
1329 InputAssumptions::kNumberOrOddball);
1330 Label<Word32> done(this);
1331
1332 IF (LIKELY(__ ObjectIsSmi(object))) {
1333 GOTO(done, __ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(object)));
1334 } ELSE {
1335 V<Float64> number_value = __ template LoadField<Float64>(
1336 object, AccessBuilder::ForHeapNumberOrOddballOrHoleValue());
1337 GOTO(done, __ JSTruncateFloat64ToWord32(number_value));
1338 }
1339
1340 BIND(done, result);
1341 return result;
1342 }
1343 case TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::UntaggedKind::kInt64: {
1344 DCHECK_EQ(input_assumptions,
1345 TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::InputAssumptions::kBigInt);
1346 DCHECK(Is64());
1347 Label<Word64> done(this);
1348
1349 V<Word32> bitfield = __ template LoadField<Word32>(
1350 object, AccessBuilder::ForBigIntBitfield());
1351 IF (__ Word32Equal(bitfield, 0)) {
1352 GOTO(done, 0);
1353 } ELSE {
1354 V<Word64> lsd = __ template LoadField<Word64>(
1355 object, AccessBuilder::ForBigIntLeastSignificantDigit64());
1356 V<Word32> sign =
1357 __ Word32BitwiseAnd(bitfield, BigInt::SignBits::kMask);
1358 IF (__ Word32Equal(sign, 1)) {
1359 GOTO(done, __ Word64Sub(0, lsd));
1360 }
1361
1362 GOTO(done, lsd);
1363 }
1364
1365 BIND(done, result);
1366 return result;
1367 }
1368 case TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::UntaggedKind::kBit: {
1369 Label<Word32> done(this);
1370
1371 if (input_assumptions ==
1372 TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::InputAssumptions::kObject) {
1373 // Perform Smi check.
1374 IF (UNLIKELY(__ ObjectIsSmi(object))) {
1375 GOTO(done, __ Word32Equal(__ TaggedEqual(object, __ TagSmi(0)), 0));
1376 }
1377
1378 // Otherwise fall through into HeapObject case.
1379 } else {
1380 DCHECK_EQ(
1381 input_assumptions,
1382 TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::InputAssumptions::kHeapObject);
1383 }
1384
1385#if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
1386 // Check if {object} is a falsey root or the true value.
1387 // Undefined is the first root, so it's the smallest possible pointer
1388 // value, which means we don't have to subtract it for the range check.
1389 ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate_);
1390 static_assert(StaticReadOnlyRoot::kFirstAllocatedRoot ==
1391 StaticReadOnlyRoot::kUndefinedValue);
1392 static_assert(StaticReadOnlyRoot::kUndefinedValue + sizeof(Undefined) ==
1393 StaticReadOnlyRoot::kNullValue);
1394 static_assert(StaticReadOnlyRoot::kNullValue + sizeof(Null) ==
1395 StaticReadOnlyRoot::kempty_string);
1396 static_assert(StaticReadOnlyRoot::kempty_string +
1397 SeqOneByteString::SizeFor(0) ==
1398 StaticReadOnlyRoot::kFalseValue);
1399 static_assert(StaticReadOnlyRoot::kFalseValue + sizeof(False) ==
1400 StaticReadOnlyRoot::kTrueValue);
1401 V<Word32> object_as_word32 = __ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(
1402 __ BitcastHeapObjectToWordPtr(V<HeapObject>::Cast(object)));
1403 V<Word32> true_as_word32 =
1404 __ Word32Constant(StaticReadOnlyRoot::kTrueValue);
1405 GOTO_IF(__ Uint32LessThan(object_as_word32, true_as_word32), done, 0);
1406 GOTO_IF(__ Word32Equal(object_as_word32, true_as_word32), done, 1);
1407#else
1408 // Check if {object} is false.
1409 GOTO_IF(
1410 __ TaggedEqual(object, __ HeapConstant(factory_->false_value())),
1411 done, 0);
1412
1413 // Check if {object} is true.
1414 GOTO_IF(__ TaggedEqual(object, __ HeapConstant(factory_->true_value())),
1415 done, 1);
1416
1417 // Check if {object} is the empty string.
1418 GOTO_IF(
1419 __ TaggedEqual(object, __ HeapConstant(factory_->empty_string())),
1420 done, 0);
1421
1422 // Only check null and undefined if we're not going to check the
1423 // undetectable bit.
1424 if (DependOnNoUndetectableObjectsProtector()) {
1425 // Check if {object} is the null value.
1426 GOTO_IF(
1427 __ TaggedEqual(object, __ HeapConstant(factory_->null_value())),
1428 done, 0);
1429
1430 // Check if {object} is the undefined value.
1431 GOTO_IF(__ TaggedEqual(object,
1432 __ HeapConstant(factory_->undefined_value())),
1433 done, 0);
1434 }
1435#endif
1436
1437 // Load the map of {object}.
1438 V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(object);
1439
1440 if (!DependOnNoUndetectableObjectsProtector()) {
1441 // Check if the {object} is undetectable and immediately return false.
1442 V<Word32> bitfield = __ template LoadField<Word32>(
1443 map, AccessBuilder::ForMapBitField());
1444 GOTO_IF(__ Word32BitwiseAnd(bitfield,
1445 Map::Bits1::IsUndetectableBit::kMask),
1446 done, 0);
1447 }
1448
1449 // Check if {object} is a HeapNumber.
1450 IF (UNLIKELY(__ TaggedEqual(
1451 map, __ HeapConstant(factory_->heap_number_map())))) {
1452 // For HeapNumber {object}, just check that its value is not 0.0, -0.0
1453 // or NaN.
1454 V<Float64> number_value =
1455 __ LoadHeapNumberValue(V<HeapNumber>::Cast(object));
1456 GOTO(done, __ Float64LessThan(0.0, __ Float64Abs(number_value)));
1457 }
1458
1459 // Check if {object} is a BigInt.
1460 IF (UNLIKELY(
1461 __ TaggedEqual(map, __ HeapConstant(factory_->bigint_map())))) {
1462 V<Word32> bitfield = __ template LoadField<Word32>(
1463 object, AccessBuilder::ForBigIntBitfield());
1464 GOTO(done, IsNonZero(__ Word32BitwiseAnd(bitfield,
1465 BigInt::LengthBits::kMask)));
1466 }
1467
1468 // All other values that reach here are true.
1469 GOTO(done, 1);
1470
1471 BIND(done, result);
1472 return result;
1473 }
1474 }
1475 UNREACHABLE();
1476 }
1477
1478 V<Word> REDUCE(TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeopt)(
1479 V<JSPrimitive> input, V<FrameState> frame_state,
1480 TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::UntaggedKind kind,
1481 TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::InputRequirement
1482 input_requirement,
1483 const FeedbackSource& feedback) {
1484 DCHECK_EQ(kind,
1485 TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::UntaggedKind::kInt32);
1486 Label<Word32> done(this);
1487 // In the Smi case, just convert to int32.
1488 GOTO_IF(LIKELY(__ ObjectIsSmi(input)), done,
1489 __ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(input)));
1490
1491 // Otherwise, check that it's a heap number or oddball and truncate the
1492 // value to int32.
1493 V<Float64> number_value = ConvertHeapObjectToFloat64OrDeopt(
1494 input, frame_state, input_requirement, feedback);
1495 GOTO(done, __ JSTruncateFloat64ToWord32(number_value));
1496
1497 BIND(done, result);
1498 return result;
1499 }
1500
1501 V<Word32> JSAnyIsNotPrimitiveHeapObject(
1502 V<Object> value, V<Map> value_map = V<Map>::Invalid()) {
1503 if (!value_map.valid()) {
1504 value_map = __ LoadMapField(value);
1505 }
1506#if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
1507 // Assumes only primitive objects and JS_RECEIVER's are passed here. All
1508 // primitive object's maps are in RO space and are allocated before all
1509 // JS_RECEIVER maps. Thus primitive object maps have smaller (compressed)
1510 // addresses.
1511 return __ Uint32LessThan(
1512 InstanceTypeChecker::kNonJsReceiverMapLimit,
1513 __ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(__ BitcastHeapObjectToWordPtr(value_map)));
1514#else
1515 static_assert(LAST_TYPE == LAST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE);
1516 V<Word32> value_instance_type = __ LoadInstanceTypeField(value_map);
1517 return __ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(FIRST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE,
1518 value_instance_type);
1519#endif
1520 }
1521
1522 V<Object> REDUCE(ConvertJSPrimitiveToObject)(V<JSPrimitive> value,
1523 V<Context> native_context,
1524 V<JSGlobalProxy> global_proxy,
1525 ConvertReceiverMode mode) {
1526 switch (mode) {
1527 case ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined:
1528 return global_proxy;
1529 case ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined:
1530 case ConvertReceiverMode::kAny: {
1531 Label<Object> done(this);
1532
1533 // Check if {value} is already a JSReceiver (or null/undefined).
1534 Label<> convert_to_object(this);
1535 GOTO_IF(UNLIKELY(__ ObjectIsSmi(value)), convert_to_object);
1536 GOTO_IF_NOT(LIKELY(__ JSAnyIsNotPrimitiveHeapObject(value)),
1537 convert_to_object);
1538 GOTO(done, value);
1539
1540 // Wrap the primitive {value} into a JSPrimitiveWrapper.
1541 if (BIND(convert_to_object)) {
1542 if (mode != ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined) {
1543 // Replace the {value} with the {global_proxy}.
1544 GOTO_IF(UNLIKELY(__ TaggedEqual(
1545 value, __ HeapConstant(factory_->undefined_value()))),
1546 done, global_proxy);
1547 GOTO_IF(UNLIKELY(__ TaggedEqual(
1548 value, __ HeapConstant(factory_->null_value()))),
1549 done, global_proxy);
1550 }
1551 GOTO(done, __ CallBuiltin_ToObject(isolate_, native_context, value));
1552 }
1553
1554 BIND(done, result);
1555 return result;
1556 }
1557 }
1558 UNREACHABLE();
1559 }
1560
1561 V<ConsString> REDUCE(NewConsString)(V<Word32> length, V<String> first,
1562 V<String> second) {
1563 // Determine the instance types of {first} and {second}.
1564 V<Map> first_map = __ LoadMapField(first);
1565 V<Word32> first_type = __ LoadInstanceTypeField(first_map);
1566 V<Map> second_map = __ LoadMapField(second);
1567 V<Word32> second_type = __ LoadInstanceTypeField(second_map);
1568
1569 Label<Map> allocate_string(this);
1570 // Determine the proper map for the resulting ConsString.
1571 // If both {first} and {second} are one-byte strings, we
1572 // create a new ConsOneByteString, otherwise we create a
1573 // new ConsString instead.
1574 static_assert(kOneByteStringTag != 0);
1575 static_assert(kTwoByteStringTag == 0);
1576 V<Word32> instance_type = __ Word32BitwiseAnd(first_type, second_type);
1577 V<Word32> encoding =
1578 __ Word32BitwiseAnd(instance_type, kStringEncodingMask);
1579 IF (__ Word32Equal(encoding, kTwoByteStringTag)) {
1580 GOTO(allocate_string,
1581 __ HeapConstant(factory_->cons_two_byte_string_map()));
1582 } ELSE {
1583 GOTO(allocate_string,
1584 __ HeapConstant(factory_->cons_one_byte_string_map()));
1585 }
1586
1587 // Allocate the resulting ConsString.
1588 BIND(allocate_string, map);
1589 auto string = __ template Allocate<ConsString>(
1590 __ IntPtrConstant(sizeof(ConsString)), AllocationType::kYoung);
1591 __ InitializeField(string, AccessBuilder::ForMap(), map);
1592 __ InitializeField(string, AccessBuilder::ForNameRawHashField(),
1593 __ Word32Constant(Name::kEmptyHashField));
1594 __ InitializeField(string, AccessBuilder::ForStringLength(), length);
1595 __ InitializeField(string, AccessBuilder::ForConsStringFirst(), first);
1596 __ InitializeField(string, AccessBuilder::ForConsStringSecond(), second);
1597 return __ FinishInitialization(std::move(string));
1598 }
1599
1600 V<AnyFixedArray> REDUCE(NewArray)(V<WordPtr> length, NewArrayOp::Kind kind,
1601 AllocationType allocation_type) {
1602 Label<AnyFixedArray> done(this);
1603
1604 GOTO_IF(__ WordPtrEqual(length, 0), done,
1605 __ HeapConstant(factory_->empty_fixed_array()));
1606
1607 // Compute the effective size of the backing store.
1608 intptr_t size_log2;
1609 Handle<Map> array_map;
1610 // TODO(nicohartmann@): Replace ElementAccess by a Turboshaft replacement.
1611 ElementAccess access;
1612 V<Any> the_hole_value;
1613 switch (kind) {
1614 case NewArrayOp::Kind::kDouble: {
1615 size_log2 = kDoubleSizeLog2;
1616 array_map = factory_->fixed_double_array_map();
1617 access = {kTaggedBase, OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(FixedDoubleArray),
1618 compiler::Type::NumberOrHole(), MachineType::Float64(),
1619 kNoWriteBarrier};
1620 the_hole_value = __ template LoadField<Float64>(
1621 __ HeapConstant(factory_->the_hole_value()),
1622 AccessBuilder::ForHeapNumberOrOddballOrHoleValue());
1623 break;
1624 }
1625 case NewArrayOp::Kind::kObject: {
1626 size_log2 = kTaggedSizeLog2;
1627 array_map = factory_->fixed_array_map();
1628 access = {kTaggedBase, OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(FixedArray),
1629 compiler::Type::Any(), MachineType::AnyTagged(),
1630 kNoWriteBarrier};
1631 the_hole_value = __ HeapConstant(factory_->the_hole_value());
1632 break;
1633 }
1634 }
1635 V<WordPtr> size =
1636 __ WordPtrAdd(__ WordPtrShiftLeft(length, static_cast<int>(size_log2)),
1637 access.header_size);
1638
1639 // Allocate the result and initialize the header.
1640 auto uninitialized_array =
1641 __ template Allocate<AnyFixedArray>(size, allocation_type);
1642 __ InitializeField(uninitialized_array, AccessBuilder::ForMap(),
1643 __ HeapConstant(array_map));
1644 __ InitializeField(uninitialized_array,
1645 AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayLength(),
1646 __ TagSmi(__ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(length)));
1647 // TODO(nicohartmann@): Should finish initialization only after all elements
1648 // have been initialized.
1649 auto array = __ FinishInitialization(std::move(uninitialized_array));
1650
1651 ScopedVar<WordPtr> index(this, 0);
1652
1653 WHILE(__ UintPtrLessThan(index, length)) {
1654 __ StoreNonArrayBufferElement(array, access, index, the_hole_value);
1655 // Advance the {index}.
1656 index = __ WordPtrAdd(index, 1);
1657 }
1658
1659 GOTO(done, array);
1660
1661 BIND(done, result);
1662 return result;
1663 }
1664
1665 V<Number> REDUCE(DoubleArrayMinMax)(V<JSArray> array,
1666 DoubleArrayMinMaxOp::Kind kind) {
1667 DCHECK(kind == DoubleArrayMinMaxOp::Kind::kMin ||
1668 kind == DoubleArrayMinMaxOp::Kind::kMax);
1669 const bool is_max = kind == DoubleArrayMinMaxOp::Kind::kMax;
1670
1671 // Iterate the elements and find the result.
1672 V<WordPtr> array_length =
1673 __ ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(__ UntagSmi(__ template LoadField<Smi>(
1674 array, AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayLength(
1675 ElementsKind::PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS))));
1676 V<Object> elements = __ template LoadField<Object>(
1677 array, AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectElements());
1678
1679 ScopedVar<Float64> result(this, is_max ? -V8_INFINITY : V8_INFINITY);
1680 ScopedVar<WordPtr> index(this, 0);
1681
1682 WHILE(__ UintPtrLessThan(index, array_length)) {
1683 V<Float64> element = __ template LoadNonArrayBufferElement<Float64>(
1684 elements, AccessBuilder::ForFixedDoubleArrayElement(), index);
1685
1686 result = is_max ? __ Float64Max(result, element)
1687 : __ Float64Min(result, element);
1688 index = __ WordPtrAdd(index, 1);
1689 }
1690
1691 return __ ConvertFloat64ToNumber(result,
1692 CheckForMinusZeroMode::kCheckForMinusZero);
1693 }
1694
1695 V<Object> REDUCE(LoadFieldByIndex)(V<Object> object, V<Word32> field_index) {
1696 // Index encoding (see `src/objects/field-index-inl.h`):
1697 // For efficiency, the LoadByFieldIndex instruction takes an index that is
1698 // optimized for quick access. If the property is inline, the index is
1699 // positive. If it's out-of-line, the encoded index is -raw_index - 1 to
1700 // disambiguate the zero out-of-line index from the zero inobject case.
1701 // The index itself is shifted up by one bit, the lower-most bit
1702 // signifying if the field is a mutable double box (1) or not (0).
1703 V<WordPtr> index = __ ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(field_index);
1704
1705 Label<> double_field(this);
1706 Label<Object> done(this);
1707
1708 // Check if field is a mutable double field.
1709 GOTO_IF(
1710 UNLIKELY(__ Word32Equal(
1711 __ Word32BitwiseAnd(__ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(index), 0x1), 0x1)),
1712 double_field);
1713
1714 {
1715 // The field is a proper Tagged field on {object}. The {index} is
1716 // shifted to the left by one in the code below.
1717
1718 // Check if field is in-object or out-of-object.
1719 IF (__ IntPtrLessThan(index, 0)) {
1720 // The field is located in the properties backing store of {object}.
1721 // The {index} is equal to the negated out of property index plus 1.
1722 V<Object> properties = __ template LoadField<Object>(
1723 object, AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectPropertiesOrHashKnownPointer());
1724
1725 V<WordPtr> out_of_object_index = __ WordPtrSub(0, index);
1726 V<Object> result =
1727 __ Load(properties, out_of_object_index,
1728 LoadOp::Kind::Aligned(BaseTaggedness::kTaggedBase),
1729 MemoryRepresentation::AnyTagged(),
1730 OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(FixedArray) - kTaggedSize,
1731 kTaggedSizeLog2 - 1);
1732 GOTO(done, result);
1733 } ELSE {
1734 // This field is located in the {object} itself.
1735 V<Object> result = __ Load(
1736 object, index, LoadOp::Kind::Aligned(BaseTaggedness::kTaggedBase),
1737 MemoryRepresentation::AnyTagged(), JSObject::kHeaderSize,
1738 kTaggedSizeLog2 - 1);
1739 GOTO(done, result);
1740 }
1741 }
1742
1743 if (BIND(double_field)) {
1744 // If field is a Double field, either unboxed in the object on 64 bit
1745 // architectures, or a mutable HeapNumber.
1746 V<WordPtr> double_index = __ WordPtrShiftRightArithmetic(index, 1);
1747 Label<Object> loaded_field(this);
1748
1749 // Check if field is in-object or out-of-object.
1750 IF (__ IntPtrLessThan(double_index, 0)) {
1751 V<Object> properties = __ template LoadField<Object>(
1752 object, AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectPropertiesOrHashKnownPointer());
1753
1754 V<WordPtr> out_of_object_index = __ WordPtrSub(0, double_index);
1755 V<Object> result = __ Load(
1756 properties, out_of_object_index,
1757 LoadOp::Kind::Aligned(BaseTaggedness::kTaggedBase),
1758 MemoryRepresentation::AnyTagged(),
1759 OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(FixedArray) - kTaggedSize, kTaggedSizeLog2);
1760 GOTO(loaded_field, result);
1761 } ELSE {
1762 // The field is located in the {object} itself.
1763 V<Object> result =
1764 __ Load(object, double_index,
1765 LoadOp::Kind::Aligned(BaseTaggedness::kTaggedBase),
1766 MemoryRepresentation::AnyTagged(), JSObject::kHeaderSize,
1767 kTaggedSizeLog2);
1768 GOTO(loaded_field, result);
1769 }
1770
1771 if (BIND(loaded_field, field)) {
1772 // We may have transitioned in-place away from double, so check that
1773 // this is a HeapNumber -- otherwise the load is fine and we don't need
1774 // to copy anything anyway.
1775 GOTO_IF(__ ObjectIsSmi(field), done, field);
1776 V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(field);
1777 GOTO_IF_NOT(
1778 __ TaggedEqual(map, __ HeapConstant(factory_->heap_number_map())),
1779 done, field);
1780
1781 V<Float64> value = __ LoadHeapNumberValue(V<HeapNumber>::Cast(field));
1782 GOTO(done, AllocateHeapNumber(value));
1783 }
1784 }
1785
1786 BIND(done, result);
1787 return result;
1788 }
1789
1790 V<Word> REDUCE(WordBinopDeoptOnOverflow)(
1791 V<Word> left, V<Word> right, V<FrameState> frame_state,
1792 WordBinopDeoptOnOverflowOp::Kind kind, WordRepresentation rep,
1793 FeedbackSource feedback, CheckForMinusZeroMode mode) {
1794 switch (kind) {
1795 case WordBinopDeoptOnOverflowOp::Kind::kSignedAdd: {
1796 DCHECK_EQ(mode, CheckForMinusZeroMode::kDontCheckForMinusZero);
1797 V<Tuple<Word, Word32>> result =
1798 __ IntAddCheckOverflow(left, right, rep);
1799
1800 V<Word32> overflow = __ template Projection<1>(result);
1801 __ DeoptimizeIf(overflow, frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kOverflow,
1802 feedback);
1803 return __ template Projection<0>(result, rep);
1804 }
1805 case WordBinopDeoptOnOverflowOp::Kind::kSignedSub: {
1806 DCHECK_EQ(mode, CheckForMinusZeroMode::kDontCheckForMinusZero);
1807 V<Tuple<Word, Word32>> result =
1808 __ IntSubCheckOverflow(left, right, rep);
1809
1810 V<Word32> overflow = __ template Projection<1>(result);
1811 __ DeoptimizeIf(overflow, frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kOverflow,
1812 feedback);
1813 return __ template Projection<0>(result, rep);
1814 }
1815 case WordBinopDeoptOnOverflowOp::Kind::kSignedMul:
1816 if (rep == WordRepresentation::Word32()) {
1817 V<Word32> left_w32 = V<Word32>::Cast(left);
1818 V<Word32> right_w32 = V<Word32>::Cast(right);
1819 V<Tuple<Word32, Word32>> result =
1820 __ Int32MulCheckOverflow(left_w32, right_w32);
1821 V<Word32> overflow = __ template Projection<1>(result);
1822 __ DeoptimizeIf(overflow, frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kOverflow,
1823 feedback);
1824 V<Word32> value = __ template Projection<0>(result);
1825
1826 if (mode == CheckForMinusZeroMode::kCheckForMinusZero) {
1827 IF (__ Word32Equal(value, 0)) {
1828 __ DeoptimizeIf(
1829 __ Int32LessThan(__ Word32BitwiseOr(left_w32, right_w32), 0),
1830 frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kMinusZero, feedback);
1831 }
1832 }
1833
1834 return value;
1835 } else {
1836 DCHECK_EQ(rep, WordRepresentation::Word64());
1837 DCHECK_EQ(mode, CheckForMinusZeroMode::kDontCheckForMinusZero);
1838 V<Tuple<Word64, Word32>> result = __ Int64MulCheckOverflow(
1839 V<Word64>::Cast(left), V<Word64>::Cast(right));
1840
1841 V<Word32> overflow = __ template Projection<1>(result);
1842 __ DeoptimizeIf(overflow, frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kOverflow,
1843 feedback);
1844 return __ template Projection<0>(result);
1845 }
1846 case WordBinopDeoptOnOverflowOp::Kind::kSignedDiv:
1847 if (rep == WordRepresentation::Word32()) {
1848 V<Word32> left_w32 = V<Word32>::Cast(left);
1849 V<Word32> right_w32 = V<Word32>::Cast(right);
1850 // Check if the {rhs} is a known power of two.
1851 int32_t divisor;
1852 if (__ matcher().MatchPowerOfTwoWord32Constant(right_w32, &divisor)) {
1853 // Since we know that {rhs} is a power of two, we can perform a fast
1854 // check to see if the relevant least significant bits of the {lhs}
1855 // are all zero, and if so we know that we can perform a division
1856 // safely (and fast by doing an arithmetic - aka sign preserving -
1857 // right shift on {lhs}).
1858 V<Word32> check =
1859 __ Word32Equal(__ Word32BitwiseAnd(left_w32, divisor - 1), 0);
1860 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(check, frame_state,
1861 DeoptimizeReason::kLostPrecision, feedback);
1862 return __ Word32ShiftRightArithmeticShiftOutZeros(
1863 left_w32, base::bits::WhichPowerOfTwo(divisor));
1864 } else {
1865 Label<Word32> done(this);
1866
1867 // Check if {rhs} is positive (and not zero).
1868 IF (__ Int32LessThan(0, right_w32)) {
1869 GOTO(done, __ Int32Div(left_w32, right_w32));
1870 } ELSE {
1871 // Check if {rhs} is zero.
1872 __ DeoptimizeIf(__ Word32Equal(right_w32, 0), frame_state,
1873 DeoptimizeReason::kDivisionByZero, feedback);
1874
1875 // Check if {lhs} is zero, as that would produce minus zero.
1876 __ DeoptimizeIf(__ Word32Equal(left_w32, 0), frame_state,
1877 DeoptimizeReason::kMinusZero, feedback);
1878
1879 // Check if {lhs} is kMinInt and {rhs} is -1, in which case we'd
1880 // have to return -kMinInt, which is not representable as Word32.
1881 IF (UNLIKELY(__ Word32Equal(left_w32, kMinInt))) {
1882 __ DeoptimizeIf(__ Word32Equal(right_w32, -1), frame_state,
1883 DeoptimizeReason::kOverflow, feedback);
1884 }
1885
1886 GOTO(done, __ Int32Div(left_w32, right_w32));
1887 }
1888
1889 BIND(done, value);
1890 V<Word32> lossless =
1891 __ Word32Equal(left_w32, __ Word32Mul(value, right_w32));
1892 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(lossless, frame_state,
1893 DeoptimizeReason::kLostPrecision, feedback);
1894 return value;
1895 }
1896 } else {
1897 DCHECK_EQ(rep, WordRepresentation::Word64());
1898 DCHECK(Is64());
1899 V<Word64> left_w64 = V<Word64>::Cast(left);
1900 V<Word64> right_w64 = V<Word64>::Cast(right);
1901
1902 __ DeoptimizeIf(__ Word64Equal(right_w64, 0), frame_state,
1903 DeoptimizeReason::kDivisionByZero, feedback);
1904 // Check if {lhs} is kMinInt64 and {rhs} is -1, in which case we'd
1905 // have to return -kMinInt64, which is not representable as Word64.
1906 IF (UNLIKELY(__ Word64Equal(left_w64,
1907 std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min()))) {
1908 __ DeoptimizeIf(__ Word64Equal(right_w64, int64_t{-1}), frame_state,
1909 DeoptimizeReason::kOverflow, feedback);
1910 }
1911
1912 return __ Int64Div(left_w64, right_w64);
1913 }
1914 case WordBinopDeoptOnOverflowOp::Kind::kSignedMod:
1915 if (rep == WordRepresentation::Word32()) {
1916 V<Word32> left_w32 = V<Word32>::Cast(left);
1917 V<Word32> right_w32 = V<Word32>::Cast(right);
1918 // General case for signed integer modulus, with optimization for
1919 // (unknown) power of 2 right hand side.
1920 //
1921 // if rhs <= 0 then
1922 // rhs = -rhs
1923 // deopt if rhs == 0
1924 // if lhs < 0 then
1925 // let lhs_abs = -lhs in
1926 // let res = lhs_abs % rhs in
1927 // deopt if res == 0
1928 // -res
1929 // else
1930 // let msk = rhs - 1 in
1931 // if rhs & msk == 0 then
1932 // lhs & msk
1933 // else
1934 // lhs % rhs
1935 //
1936 Label<Word32> rhs_checked(this);
1937 Label<Word32> done(this);
1938
1939 // Check if {rhs} is not strictly positive.
1940 IF (__ Int32LessThanOrEqual(right_w32, 0)) {
1941 // Negate {rhs}, might still produce a negative result in case of
1942 // -2^31, but that is handled safely below.
1943 V<Word32> temp = __ Word32Sub(0, right_w32);
1944
1945 // Ensure that {rhs} is not zero, otherwise we'd have to return NaN.
1946 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(temp, frame_state,
1947 DeoptimizeReason::kDivisionByZero, feedback);
1948 GOTO(rhs_checked, temp);
1949 } ELSE {
1950 GOTO(rhs_checked, right_w32);
1951 }
1952
1953 BIND(rhs_checked, rhs_value);
1954
1955 IF (__ Int32LessThan(left_w32, 0)) {
1956 // The {lhs} is a negative integer. This is very unlikely and
1957 // we intentionally don't use the BuildUint32Mod() here, which
1958 // would try to figure out whether {rhs} is a power of two,
1959 // since this is intended to be a slow-path.
1960 V<Word32> temp = __ Uint32Mod(__ Word32Sub(0, left_w32), rhs_value);
1961
1962 // Check if we would have to return -0.
1963 __ DeoptimizeIf(__ Word32Equal(temp, 0), frame_state,
1964 DeoptimizeReason::kMinusZero, feedback);
1965 GOTO(done, __ Word32Sub(0, temp));
1966 } ELSE {
1967 // The {lhs} is a non-negative integer.
1968 GOTO(done, BuildUint32Mod(left_w32, rhs_value));
1969 }
1970
1971 BIND(done, result);
1972 return result;
1973 } else {
1974 DCHECK_EQ(rep, WordRepresentation::Word64());
1975 DCHECK(Is64());
1976 V<Word64> left_w64 = V<Word64>::Cast(left);
1977 V<Word64> right_w64 = V<Word64>::Cast(right);
1978
1979 __ DeoptimizeIf(__ Word64Equal(right_w64, 0), frame_state,
1980 DeoptimizeReason::kDivisionByZero, feedback);
1981
1982 // While the mod-result cannot overflow, the underlying instruction is
1983 // `idiv` and will trap when the accompanying div-result overflows.
1984 IF (UNLIKELY(__ Word64Equal(left_w64,
1985 std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min()))) {
1986 __ DeoptimizeIf(__ Word64Equal(right_w64, int64_t{-1}), frame_state,
1987 DeoptimizeReason::kOverflow, feedback);
1988 }
1989
1990 return __ Int64Mod(left_w64, right_w64);
1991 }
1992 case WordBinopDeoptOnOverflowOp::Kind::kUnsignedDiv: {
1993 DCHECK_EQ(rep, WordRepresentation::Word32());
1994 V<Word32> left_w32 = V<Word32>::Cast(left);
1995 V<Word32> right_w32 = V<Word32>::Cast(right);
1996
1997 // Check if the {rhs} is a known power of two.
1998 int32_t divisor;
1999 if (__ matcher().MatchPowerOfTwoWord32Constant(right_w32, &divisor)) {
2000 // Since we know that {rhs} is a power of two, we can perform a fast
2001 // check to see if the relevant least significant bits of the {lhs}
2002 // are all zero, and if so we know that we can perform a division
2003 // safely (and fast by doing a logical - aka zero extending - right
2004 // shift on {lhs}).
2005 V<Word32> check =
2006 __ Word32Equal(__ Word32BitwiseAnd(left_w32, divisor - 1), 0);
2007 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(check, frame_state,
2008 DeoptimizeReason::kLostPrecision, feedback);
2009 return __ Word32ShiftRightLogical(
2010 left_w32, base::bits::WhichPowerOfTwo(divisor));
2011 } else {
2012 // Ensure that {rhs} is not zero, otherwise we'd have to return NaN.
2013 __ DeoptimizeIf(__ Word32Equal(right_w32, 0), frame_state,
2014 DeoptimizeReason::kDivisionByZero, feedback);
2015
2016 // Perform the actual unsigned integer division.
2017 V<Word32> value = __ Uint32Div(left_w32, right_w32);
2018
2019 // Check if the remainder is non-zero.
2020 V<Word32> lossless =
2021 __ Word32Equal(left_w32, __ Word32Mul(right_w32, value));
2022 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(lossless, frame_state,
2023 DeoptimizeReason::kLostPrecision, feedback);
2024 return value;
2025 }
2026 }
2027 case WordBinopDeoptOnOverflowOp::Kind::kUnsignedMod: {
2028 DCHECK_EQ(rep, WordRepresentation::Word32());
2029 V<Word32> left_w32 = V<Word32>::Cast(left);
2030 V<Word32> right_w32 = V<Word32>::Cast(right);
2031
2032 // Ensure that {rhs} is not zero, otherwise we'd have to return NaN.
2033 __ DeoptimizeIf(__ Word32Equal(right_w32, 0), frame_state,
2034 DeoptimizeReason::kDivisionByZero, feedback);
2035
2036 return BuildUint32Mod(left_w32, right_w32);
2037 }
2038 }
2039 }
2040
2041 V<BigInt> REDUCE(BigIntBinop)(V<BigInt> left, V<BigInt> right,
2042 V<FrameState> frame_state,
2043 BigIntBinopOp::Kind kind) {
2044 const Builtin builtin = GetBuiltinForBigIntBinop(kind);
2045 switch (kind) {
2046 case BigIntBinopOp::Kind::kAdd:
2047 case BigIntBinopOp::Kind::kSub:
2048 case BigIntBinopOp::Kind::kBitwiseAnd:
2049 case BigIntBinopOp::Kind::kBitwiseXor:
2050 case BigIntBinopOp::Kind::kShiftLeft:
2051 case BigIntBinopOp::Kind::kShiftRightArithmetic: {
2052 V<Numeric> result = CallBuiltinForBigIntOp(builtin, {left, right});
2053
2054 // Check for exception sentinel: Smi 0 is returned to signal
2055 // BigIntTooBig.
2056 __ DeoptimizeIf(__ ObjectIsSmi(result), frame_state,
2057 DeoptimizeReason::kBigIntTooBig, FeedbackSource{});
2058 return V<BigInt>::Cast(result);
2059 }
2060 case BigIntBinopOp::Kind::kMul:
2061 case BigIntBinopOp::Kind::kDiv:
2062 case BigIntBinopOp::Kind::kMod: {
2063 V<Numeric> result = CallBuiltinForBigIntOp(builtin, {left, right});
2064
2065 // Check for exception sentinel: Smi 1 is returned to signal
2066 // TerminationRequested.
2067 IF (UNLIKELY(__ TaggedEqual(result, __ TagSmi(1)))) {
2068 __ CallRuntime_TerminateExecution(isolate_, frame_state,
2069 __ NoContextConstant());
2070 }
2071
2072 // Check for exception sentinel: Smi 0 is returned to signal
2073 // BigIntTooBig or DivisionByZero.
2074 __ DeoptimizeIf(__ ObjectIsSmi(result), frame_state,
2075 kind == BigIntBinopOp::Kind::kMul
2076 ? DeoptimizeReason::kBigIntTooBig
2077 : DeoptimizeReason::kDivisionByZero,
2078 FeedbackSource{});
2079 return V<BigInt>::Cast(result);
2080 }
2081 case BigIntBinopOp::Kind::kBitwiseOr: {
2082 return CallBuiltinForBigIntOp(builtin, {left, right});
2083 }
2084 default:
2085 UNIMPLEMENTED();
2086 }
2087 UNREACHABLE();
2088 }
2089
2090 V<Boolean> REDUCE(BigIntComparison)(V<BigInt> left, V<BigInt> right,
2091 BigIntComparisonOp::Kind kind) {
2092 switch (kind) {
2093 case BigIntComparisonOp::Kind::kEqual:
2094 return CallBuiltinForBigIntOp(Builtin::kBigIntEqual, {left, right});
2095 case BigIntComparisonOp::Kind::kLessThan:
2096 return CallBuiltinForBigIntOp(Builtin::kBigIntLessThan, {left, right});
2097 case BigIntComparisonOp::Kind::kLessThanOrEqual:
2098 return CallBuiltinForBigIntOp(Builtin::kBigIntLessThanOrEqual,
2099 {left, right});
2100 }
2101 }

2103 V<BigInt> REDUCE(BigIntUnary)(V<BigInt> input, BigIntUnaryOp::Kind kind) {
2104 DCHECK_EQ(kind, BigIntUnaryOp::Kind::kNegate);
2105 return CallBuiltinForBigIntOp(Builtin::kBigIntUnaryMinus, {input});
2106 }
