2108 V<Word32> REDUCE(StringAt)(V<String> string, V<WordPtr> pos,
2109 StringAtOp::Kind kind) {
2110 if (kind == StringAtOp::Kind::kCharCode) {
2111 Label<Word32> done(this);
2112
2113 if (const ConstantOp* cst =
2114 __ matcher().template TryCast<ConstantOp>(string);
2115 cst && cst->kind == ConstantOp::Kind::kHeapObject) {
2116 // For constant SeqString, we have a fast-path that doesn't run through
2117 // the loop. It requires fewer loads (we only load the map once, but not
2118 // the instance type), uses static 1/2-byte, and only uses a single
2119 // comparison to check that the string has indeed the correct SeqString
2120 // map.
2121 UnparkedScopeIfNeeded unpark(broker_);
2122 HeapObjectRef ref = MakeRef(broker_, cst->handle());
2123 if (ref.IsString()) {
2124 StringRef str = ref.AsString();
2125 if (str.IsSeqString()) {
2126 V<Map> dynamic_map = __ LoadMapField(string);
2127 Handle<Map> expected_map = str.map(broker_).object();
2128 IF (__ TaggedEqual(dynamic_map, __ HeapConstant(expected_map))) {
2129 bool one_byte = str.IsOneByteRepresentation();
2130 GOTO(done,
2131 LoadFromSeqString(string, pos, __ Word32Constant(one_byte)));
2132 }
2133 }
2134 }
2135 }
2136
2137 Label<> seq_string(this), external_string(this), cons_string(this),
2138 sliced_string(this), thin_string(this);
2139 // TODO(dmercadier): the runtime label should be deferred, and because
2140 // Labels/Blocks don't have deferred annotation, we achieve this by
2141 // marking all branches to this Label as UNLIKELY, but 1) it's easy to
2142 // forget one, and 2) it makes the code less clear: `if(x) {} else
2143 // if(likely(y)) {} else {}` looks like `y` is more likely than `x`, but
2144 // it just means that `y` is more likely than `!y`.
2145 Label<> runtime(this);
2146 // We need a loop here to properly deal with indirect strings
2147 // (SlicedString, ConsString and ThinString).
2148 LoopLabel<> loop(this);
2149 ScopedVar<String> receiver(this, string);
2150 ScopedVar<WordPtr> position(this, pos);
2151 GOTO(loop);
2152
2153 BIND_LOOP(loop) {
2154 V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(receiver);
2155#if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
2156 V<Word32> map_bits =
2157 __ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(__ BitcastTaggedToWordPtr(map));
2158
2159 using StringTypeRange =
2160 InstanceTypeChecker::kUniqueMapRangeOfStringType;
2161 // Check the string map ranges in dense increasing order, to avoid
2162 // needing to subtract away the lower bound.
2163 static_assert(StringTypeRange::kSeqString.first == 0);
2164 GOTO_IF(__ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(map_bits,
2165 StringTypeRange::kSeqString.second),
2166 seq_string);
2167
2168 static_assert(StringTypeRange::kSeqString.second + Map::kSize ==
2169 StringTypeRange::kExternalString.first);
2170 GOTO_IF(__ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(
2171 map_bits, StringTypeRange::kExternalString.second),
2172 external_string);
2173
2174 static_assert(StringTypeRange::kExternalString.second + Map::kSize ==
2175 StringTypeRange::kConsString.first);
2176 GOTO_IF(__ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(map_bits,
2177 StringTypeRange::kConsString.second),
2178 cons_string);
2179
2180 static_assert(StringTypeRange::kConsString.second + Map::kSize ==
2181 StringTypeRange::kSlicedString.first);
2182 GOTO_IF(__ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(map_bits,
2183 StringTypeRange::kSlicedString.second),
2184 sliced_string);
2185
2186 static_assert(StringTypeRange::kSlicedString.second + Map::kSize ==
2187 StringTypeRange::kThinString.first);
2188 GOTO_IF(__ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(map_bits,
2189 StringTypeRange::kThinString.second),
2190 thin_string);
2191#else
2192 V<Word32> instance_type = __ LoadInstanceTypeField(map);
2193 V<Word32> representation =
2194 __ Word32BitwiseAnd(instance_type, kStringRepresentationMask);
2195
2196 GOTO_IF(__ Word32Equal(representation, kSeqStringTag), seq_string);
2197 GOTO_IF(__ Word32Equal(representation, kExternalStringTag),
2198 external_string);
2199 GOTO_IF(__ Word32Equal(representation, kConsStringTag), cons_string);
2200 GOTO_IF(__ Word32Equal(representation, kSlicedStringTag),
2201 sliced_string);
2202 GOTO_IF(__ Word32Equal(representation, kThinStringTag), thin_string);
2203#endif
2204
2205 __ Unreachable();
2206
2207 if (BIND(seq_string)) {
2208#if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
2209 V<Word32> is_one_byte = __ Word32Equal(
2210 __ Word32BitwiseAnd(map_bits,
2211 InstanceTypeChecker::kStringMapEncodingMask),
2212 InstanceTypeChecker::kOneByteStringMapBit);
2213#else
2214 V<Word32> is_one_byte = __ Word32Equal(
2215 __ Word32BitwiseAnd(instance_type, kStringEncodingMask),
2216 kOneByteStringTag);
2217#endif
2218 GOTO(done, LoadFromSeqString(receiver, position, is_one_byte));
2219 }
2220
2221 if (BIND(external_string)) {
2222 // We need to bailout to the runtime for uncached external
2223 // strings.
2224#if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
2225 V<Word32> is_uncached_external_string = __ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(
2226 __ Word32Sub(map_bits,
2227 StringTypeRange::kUncachedExternalString.first),
2228 StringTypeRange::kUncachedExternalString.second -
2229 StringTypeRange::kUncachedExternalString.first);
2230#else
2231 V<Word32> is_uncached_external_string = __ Word32Equal(
2232 __ Word32BitwiseAnd(instance_type, kUncachedExternalStringMask),
2233 kUncachedExternalStringTag);
2234#endif
2235 GOTO_IF(UNLIKELY(is_uncached_external_string), runtime);
2236
2237 OpIndex data = __ LoadField(
2238 receiver, AccessBuilder::ForExternalStringResourceData());
2239#if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
2240 V<Word32> is_two_byte = __ Word32Equal(
2241 __ Word32BitwiseAnd(map_bits,
2242 InstanceTypeChecker::kStringMapEncodingMask),
2243 InstanceTypeChecker::kTwoByteStringMapBit);
2244#else
2245 V<Word32> is_two_byte = __ Word32Equal(
2246 __ Word32BitwiseAnd(instance_type, kStringEncodingMask),
2247 kTwoByteStringTag);
2248#endif
2249 IF (is_two_byte) {
2250 constexpr uint8_t twobyte_size_log2 = 1;
2251 V<Word32> value =
2252 __ Load(data, position,
2253 LoadOp::Kind::Aligned(BaseTaggedness::kUntaggedBase),
2254 MemoryRepresentation::Uint16(), 0, twobyte_size_log2);
2255 GOTO(done, value);
2256 } ELSE {
2257 constexpr uint8_t onebyte_size_log2 = 0;
2258 V<Word32> value =
2259 __ Load(data, position,
2260 LoadOp::Kind::Aligned(BaseTaggedness::kUntaggedBase),
2261 MemoryRepresentation::Uint8(), 0, onebyte_size_log2);
2262 GOTO(done, value);
2263 }
2264 }
2265
2266 if (BIND(cons_string)) {
2267 V<String> second = __ template LoadField<String>(
2268 receiver, AccessBuilder::ForConsStringSecond());
2269 GOTO_IF_NOT(LIKELY(__ TaggedEqual(
2270 second, __ HeapConstant(factory_->empty_string()))),
2271 runtime);
2272 receiver = __ template LoadField<String>(
2273 receiver, AccessBuilder::ForConsStringFirst());
2274 GOTO(loop);
2275 }
2276
2277 if (BIND(sliced_string)) {
2278 V<Smi> offset = __ template LoadField<Smi>(
2279 receiver, AccessBuilder::ForSlicedStringOffset());
2280 receiver = __ template LoadField<String>(
2281 receiver, AccessBuilder::ForSlicedStringParent());
2282 position = __ WordPtrAdd(position,
2283 __ ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(__ UntagSmi(offset)));
2284 GOTO(loop);
2285 }
2286
2287 if (BIND(thin_string)) {
2288 receiver = __ template LoadField<String>(
2289 receiver, AccessBuilder::ForThinStringActual());
2290 GOTO(loop);
2291 }
2292
2293 if (BIND(runtime)) {
2294 V<Word32> value =
2295 __ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(__ CallRuntime_StringCharCodeAt(
2296 isolate_, __ NoContextConstant(), receiver,
2297 __ TagSmi(__ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(position)))));
2298 GOTO(done, value);
2299 }
2300 }
2301
2302 BIND(done, result);
2303 return result;
2304 } else {
2305 DCHECK_EQ(kind, StringAtOp::Kind::kCodePoint);
2306 return LoadSurrogatePairAt(string, {}, pos, UnicodeEncoding::UTF32);
2307 }
2308
2309 UNREACHABLE();
2310 }

2314 // SimplifiedOptimizationReducer?), constant fold StringLength(Constant).
2315 return __ template LoadField<Word32>(string,
2316 AccessBuilder::ForStringLength());

2355
2356 V<Boolean> REDUCE(StringComparison)(V<String> left, V<String> right,
2357 StringComparisonOp::Kind kind) {
2358 switch (kind) {
2359 case StringComparisonOp::Kind::kEqual: {
2360 Label<Boolean> done(this);
2361
2362 GOTO_IF(__ TaggedEqual(left, right), done,
2363 __ HeapConstant(factory_->true_value()));
2364
2365 V<Word32> left_length = __ template LoadField<Word32>(
2366 left, AccessBuilder::ForStringLength());
2367 V<Word32> right_length = __ template LoadField<Word32>(
2368 right, AccessBuilder::ForStringLength());
2369 IF (__ Word32Equal(left_length, right_length)) {
2370 GOTO(done,
2371 __ CallBuiltin_StringEqual(isolate_, left, right,
2372 __ ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(left_length)));
2373 } ELSE {
2374 GOTO(done, __ HeapConstant(factory_->false_value()));
2375 }
2376
2377 BIND(done, result);
2378 return result;
2379 }
2380 case StringComparisonOp::Kind::kLessThan:
2381 return __ CallBuiltin_StringLessThan(isolate_, left, right);
2382 case StringComparisonOp::Kind::kLessThanOrEqual:
2383 return __ CallBuiltin_StringLessThanOrEqual(isolate_, left, right);
2384 }
2385 }
2386
2387 V<Smi> REDUCE(ArgumentsLength)(ArgumentsLengthOp::Kind kind,
2388 int formal_parameter_count) {
2389 V<WordPtr> count =
2390 __ LoadOffHeap(__ FramePointer(), StandardFrameConstants::kArgCOffset,
2391 MemoryRepresentation::UintPtr());
2392 V<WordPtr> arguments_length = __ WordPtrSub(count, kJSArgcReceiverSlots);
2393
2394 if (kind == ArgumentsLengthOp::Kind::kArguments) {
2395 return __ TagSmi(__ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(arguments_length));
2396 } else {
2397 DCHECK_EQ(kind, ArgumentsLengthOp::Kind::kRest);
2398 V<WordPtr> rest_length =
2399 __ WordPtrSub(arguments_length, formal_parameter_count);
2400 Label<WordPtr> done(this);
2401 IF (__ IntPtrLessThan(rest_length, 0)) {
2402 GOTO(done, 0);
2403 } ELSE {
2404 GOTO(done, rest_length);
2405 }
2406
2407 BIND(done, value);
2408 return __ TagSmi(__ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(value));
2409 }
2410 }
2411
2412 V<Object> REDUCE(NewArgumentsElements)(V<Smi> arguments_count,
2413 CreateArgumentsType type,
2414 int formal_parameter_count) {
2415 V<WordPtr> frame = __ FramePointer();
2416 V<WordPtr> p_count = __ IntPtrConstant(formal_parameter_count);
2417 switch (type) {
2418 case CreateArgumentsType::kMappedArguments:
2419 return __ CallBuiltin_NewSloppyArgumentsElements(
2420 isolate_, frame, p_count, arguments_count);
2421 case CreateArgumentsType::kUnmappedArguments:
2422 return __ CallBuiltin_NewStrictArgumentsElements(
2423 isolate_, frame, p_count, arguments_count);
2424 case CreateArgumentsType::kRestParameter:
2425 return __ CallBuiltin_NewRestArgumentsElements(isolate_, frame, p_count,
2426 arguments_count);
2427 }
2428 }
2429
2430 V<Any> REDUCE(LoadTypedElement)(OpIndex buffer, V<Object> base,
2431 V<WordPtr> external, V<WordPtr> index,
2432 ExternalArrayType array_type) {
2433 V<WordPtr> data_ptr = BuildTypedArrayDataPointer(base, external);
2434
2435 // Perform the actual typed element access.
2436 V<Any> result = __ LoadArrayBufferElement(
2437 data_ptr, AccessBuilder::ForTypedArrayElement(array_type, true), index);
2438
2439 // We need to keep the {buffer} alive so that the GC will not release the
2440 // ArrayBuffer (if there's any) as long as we are still operating on it.
2441 __ Retain(buffer);
2442 return result;
2443 }
2444
2445 V<Object> REDUCE(LoadStackArgument)(V<WordPtr> base, V<WordPtr> index) {
2446 // Note that this is a load of a Tagged value
2447 // (MemoryRepresentation::TaggedPointer()), but since it's on the stack
2448 // where stack slots are all kSystemPointerSize, we use kSystemPointerSize
2449 // for element_size_log2. On 64-bit plateforms with pointer compression,
2450 // this means that we're kinda loading a 32-bit value from an array of
2451 // 64-bit values.
2452#if V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS && V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN
2453 constexpr int offset =
2454 CommonFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeAboveFp - kSystemPointerSize + 4;
2455#else
2456 constexpr int offset =
2457 CommonFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeAboveFp - kSystemPointerSize;
2458#endif
2459 return __ Load(base, index, LoadOp::Kind::RawAligned(),
2460 MemoryRepresentation::TaggedPointer(), offset,
2461 kSystemPointerSizeLog2);
2462 }
2463
2464 V<None> REDUCE(StoreTypedElement)(OpIndex buffer, V<Object> base,
2465 V<WordPtr> external, V<WordPtr> index,
2466 V<Any> value,
2467 ExternalArrayType array_type) {
2468 V<WordPtr> data_ptr = BuildTypedArrayDataPointer(base, external);
2469
2470 // Perform the actual typed element access.
2471 __ StoreArrayBufferElement(
2472 data_ptr, AccessBuilder::ForTypedArrayElement(array_type, true), index,
2473 value);
2474
2475 // We need to keep the {buffer} alive so that the GC will not release the
2476 // ArrayBuffer (if there's any) as long as we are still operating on it.
2477 __ Retain(buffer);
2478 return {};
2479 }
2480
2481 V<None> REDUCE(TransitionAndStoreArrayElement)(
2482 V<JSArray> array, V<WordPtr> index, OpIndex value,
2483 TransitionAndStoreArrayElementOp::Kind kind, MaybeHandle<Map> fast_map,
2484 MaybeHandle<Map> double_map) {
2485 V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(array);
2486 V<Word32> bitfield2 =
2487 __ template LoadField<Word32>(map, AccessBuilder::ForMapBitField2());
2488 V<Word32> elements_kind = __ Word32ShiftRightLogical(
2489 __ Word32BitwiseAnd(bitfield2, Map::Bits2::ElementsKindBits::kMask),
2490 Map::Bits2::ElementsKindBits::kShift);
2491
2492 switch (kind) {
2493 case TransitionAndStoreArrayElementOp::Kind::kElement: {
2494 // Possibly transition array based on input and store.
2495 //
2496 // -- TRANSITION PHASE -----------------
2497 // kind = ElementsKind(array)
2498 // if value is not smi {
2499 // if kind == HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS {
2500 // if value is heap number {
2501 // Transition array to HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS
2502 // kind = HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS
2503 // } else {
2504 // Transition array to HOLEY_ELEMENTS
2505 // kind = HOLEY_ELEMENTS
2506 // }
2507 // } else if kind == HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS {
2508 // if value is not heap number {
2509 // Transition array to HOLEY_ELEMENTS
2510 // kind = HOLEY_ELEMENTS
2511 // }
2512 // }
2513 // }
2514 //
2515 // -- STORE PHASE ----------------------
2516 // [make sure {kind} is up-to-date]
2517 // if kind == HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS {
2518 // if value is smi {
2519 // float_value = convert smi to float
2520 // Store array[index] = float_value
2521 // } else {
2522 // float_value = value
2523 // Store array[index] = float_value
2524 // }
2525 // } else {
2526 // // kind is HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS or HOLEY_ELEMENTS
2527 // Store array[index] = value
2528 // }
2529 //
2530 Label<Word32> do_store(this);
2531 // We can store a smi anywhere.
2532 GOTO_IF(__ ObjectIsSmi(value), do_store, elements_kind);
2533
2534 // {value} is a HeapObject.
2535 IF_NOT (LIKELY(__ Int32LessThan(HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS, elements_kind))) {
2536 // Transition {array} from HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS to HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS
2537 // or to HOLEY_ELEMENTS.
2538 V<Map> value_map = __ LoadMapField(value);
2539 IF (__ TaggedEqual(value_map,
2540 __ HeapConstant(factory_->heap_number_map()))) {
2541 // {value} is a HeapNumber.
2542 TransitionElementsTo(array, HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS,
2543 HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS,
2544 double_map.ToHandleChecked());
2545 GOTO(do_store, HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS);
2546 } ELSE {
2547 TransitionElementsTo(array, HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS, HOLEY_ELEMENTS,
2548 fast_map.ToHandleChecked());
2549 GOTO(do_store, HOLEY_ELEMENTS);
2550 }
2551 }
2552
2553 GOTO_IF_NOT(LIKELY(__ Int32LessThan(HOLEY_ELEMENTS, elements_kind)),
2554 do_store, elements_kind);
2555
2556 // We have double elements kind. Only a HeapNumber can be stored
2557 // without effecting a transition.
2558 V<Map> value_map = __ LoadMapField(value);
2559 IF_NOT (UNLIKELY(__ TaggedEqual(
2560 value_map, __ HeapConstant(factory_->heap_number_map())))) {
2561 TransitionElementsTo(array, HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS, HOLEY_ELEMENTS,
2562 fast_map.ToHandleChecked());
2563 GOTO(do_store, HOLEY_ELEMENTS);
2564 }
2565
2566 GOTO(do_store, elements_kind);
2567
2568 BIND(do_store, store_kind);
2569 V<Object> elements = __ template LoadField<Object>(
2570 array, AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectElements());
2571 IF (__ Int32LessThan(HOLEY_ELEMENTS, store_kind)) {
2572 // Our ElementsKind is HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS.
2573 IF (__ ObjectIsSmi(value)) {
2574 V<Float64> float_value =
2575 __ ChangeInt32ToFloat64(__ UntagSmi(value));
2576 __ StoreNonArrayBufferElement(
2577 elements, AccessBuilder::ForFixedDoubleArrayElement(), index,
2578 float_value);
2579 } ELSE {
2580 V<Float64> float_value =
2581 __ LoadHeapNumberValue(V<HeapNumber>::Cast(value));
2582 __ StoreNonArrayBufferElement(
2583 elements, AccessBuilder::ForFixedDoubleArrayElement(), index,
2584 __ Float64SilenceNaN(float_value));
2585 }
2586 } ELSE {
2587 // Our ElementsKind is HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS or HOLEY_ELEMENTS.
2588 __ StoreNonArrayBufferElement(
2589 elements, AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement(HOLEY_ELEMENTS),
2590 index, value);
2591 }
2592
2593 break;
2594 }
2595 case TransitionAndStoreArrayElementOp::Kind::kNumberElement: {
2596 Label<> done(this);
2597 // Possibly transition array based on input and store.
2598 //
2599 // -- TRANSITION PHASE -----------------
2600 // kind = ElementsKind(array)
2601 // if kind == HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS {
2602 // Transition array to HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS
2603 // } else if kind != HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS {
2604 // if kind == HOLEY_ELEMENTS {
2605 // Store value as a HeapNumber in array[index].
2606 // } else {
2607 // This is UNREACHABLE, execute a debug break.
2608 // }
2609 // }
2610 //
2611 // -- STORE PHASE ----------------------
2612 // Store array[index] = value (it's a float)
2613 //
2614 // {value} is a float64.
2615 IF_NOT (LIKELY(__ Int32LessThan(HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS, elements_kind))) {
2616 // Transition {array} from HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS to
2617 // HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS.
2618 TransitionElementsTo(array, HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS, HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS,
2619 double_map.ToHandleChecked());
2620 } ELSE {
2621 // We expect that our input array started at HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS, and
2622 // climbs the lattice up to HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS. However, loop
2623 // peeling can break this assumption, because in the peeled iteration,
2624 // the array might have transitioned to HOLEY_ELEMENTS kind, so we
2625 // handle this as well.
2626 IF_NOT (LIKELY(
2627 __ Word32Equal(elements_kind, HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS))) {
2628 IF (__ Word32Equal(elements_kind, HOLEY_ELEMENTS)) {
2629 V<Object> elements = __ template LoadField<Object>(
2630 array, AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectElements());
2631 // Our ElementsKind is HOLEY_ELEMENTS.
2632 __ StoreNonArrayBufferElement(
2633 elements, AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement(HOLEY_ELEMENTS),
2634 index, AllocateHeapNumber(value));
2635 GOTO(done);
2636 }
2637
2638 __ Unreachable();
2639 }
2640 }
2641
2642 V<Object> elements = __ template LoadField<Object>(
2643 array, AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectElements());
2644 __ StoreNonArrayBufferElement(
2645 elements, AccessBuilder::ForFixedDoubleArrayElement(), index,
2646 __ Float64SilenceNaN(value));
2647 GOTO(done);
2648
2649 BIND(done);
2650 break;
2651 }
2652 case TransitionAndStoreArrayElementOp::Kind::kOddballElement:
2653 case TransitionAndStoreArrayElementOp::Kind::kNonNumberElement: {
2654 // Possibly transition array based on input and store.
2655 //
2656 // -- TRANSITION PHASE -----------------
2657 // kind = ElementsKind(array)
2658 // if kind == HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS {
2659 // Transition array to HOLEY_ELEMENTS
2660 // } else if kind == HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS {
2661 // Transition array to HOLEY_ELEMENTS
2662 // }
2663 //
2664 // -- STORE PHASE ----------------------
2665 // // kind is HOLEY_ELEMENTS
2666 // Store array[index] = value
2667 //
2668 IF_NOT (LIKELY(__ Int32LessThan(HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS, elements_kind))) {
2669 // Transition {array} from HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS to HOLEY_ELEMENTS.
2670 TransitionElementsTo(array, HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS, HOLEY_ELEMENTS,
2671 fast_map.ToHandleChecked());
2672 } ELSE IF (UNLIKELY(__ Int32LessThan(HOLEY_ELEMENTS, elements_kind))) {
2673 TransitionElementsTo(array, HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS, HOLEY_ELEMENTS,
2674 fast_map.ToHandleChecked());
2675 }
2676
2677 V<Object> elements = __ template LoadField<Object>(
2678 array, AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectElements());
2679 ElementAccess access =
2680 AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement(HOLEY_ELEMENTS);
2681 if (kind == TransitionAndStoreArrayElementOp::Kind::kOddballElement) {
2682 access.type = compiler::Type::BooleanOrNullOrUndefined();
2683 access.write_barrier_kind = kNoWriteBarrier;
2684 }
2685 __ StoreNonArrayBufferElement(elements, access, index, value);
2686 break;
2687 }
2688 case TransitionAndStoreArrayElementOp::Kind::kSignedSmallElement: {
2689 // Store a signed small in an output array.
2690 //
2691 // kind = ElementsKind(array)
2692 //
2693 // -- STORE PHASE ----------------------
2694 // if kind == HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS {
2695 // float_value = convert int32 to float
2696 // Store array[index] = float_value
2697 // } else {
2698 // // kind is HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS or HOLEY_ELEMENTS
2699 // smi_value = convert int32 to smi
2700 // Store array[index] = smi_value
2701 // }
2702 //
2703 V<Object> elements = __ template LoadField<Object>(
2704 array, AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectElements());
2705 IF (__ Int32LessThan(HOLEY_ELEMENTS, elements_kind)) {
2706 // Our ElementsKind is HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS.
2707 V<Float64> f64 = __ ChangeInt32ToFloat64(value);
2708 __ StoreNonArrayBufferElement(
2709 elements, AccessBuilder::ForFixedDoubleArrayElement(), index,
2710 f64);
2711 } ELSE {
2712 // Our ElementsKind is HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS or HOLEY_ELEMENTS.
2713 // In this case, we know our value is a signed small, and we can
2714 // optimize the ElementAccess information.
2715 ElementAccess access = AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement();
2716 access.type = compiler::Type::SignedSmall();
2717 access.machine_type = MachineType::TaggedSigned();
2718 access.write_barrier_kind = kNoWriteBarrier;
2719 __ StoreNonArrayBufferElement(elements, access, index,
2720 __ TagSmi(value));
2721 }
2722
2723 break;
2724 }
2725 }
2726
2727 return V<None>::Invalid();
2728 }
2729
2730 V<Word32> REDUCE(CompareMaps)(V<HeapObject> heap_object, OptionalV<Map> map,
2731 const ZoneRefSet<Map>& maps) {
2732 if (!map.has_value()) {
2733 map = __ LoadMapField(heap_object);
2734 }
2735 return CompareMapAgainstMultipleMaps(map.value(), maps);
2736 }
2737
2738 V<None> REDUCE(CheckMaps)(V<HeapObject> heap_object,
2739 V<FrameState> frame_state, OptionalV<Map> map,
2740 const ZoneRefSet<Map>& maps, CheckMapsFlags flags,
2741 const FeedbackSource& feedback) {
2742 if (maps.is_empty()) {
2743 __ Deoptimize(frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap, feedback);
2744 return {};
2745 }
2746
2747 V<Map> heap_object_map;
2748 if (map.has_value()) {
2749 heap_object_map = map.value();
2750 } else {
2751 heap_object_map = __ LoadMapField(heap_object);
2752 }
2753
2754 if (flags & CheckMapsFlag::kTryMigrateInstance) {
2755 IF_NOT (LIKELY(CompareMapAgainstMultipleMaps(heap_object_map, maps))) {
2756 // Reloading the map slightly reduces register pressure, and we are on a
2757 // slow path here anyway.
2758 MigrateInstanceOrDeopt(heap_object, heap_object_map, frame_state,
2759 feedback);
2760 heap_object_map = __ LoadMapField(heap_object);
2761 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(__ CompareMaps(heap_object, heap_object_map, maps),
2762 frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap, feedback);
2763 }
2764 } else if (flags & CheckMapsFlag::kTryMigrateInstanceAndDeopt) {
2765 IF_NOT (LIKELY(CompareMapAgainstMultipleMaps(heap_object_map, maps))) {
2766 TryMigrateInstanceAndMarkMapAsMigrationTarget(
2767 heap_object, heap_object_map, frame_state, feedback);
2768 __ Deoptimize(frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap, feedback);
2769 }
2770 } else {
2771 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(__ CompareMaps(heap_object, heap_object_map, maps),
2772 frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap, feedback);
2773 }
2774 // Inserting a AssumeMap so that subsequent optimizations know the map of
2775 // this object.
2776 __ AssumeMap(heap_object, maps);
2777 return {};
2778 }
2779
2780 V<Float> REDUCE(FloatUnary)(V<Float> input, FloatUnaryOp::Kind kind,
2781 FloatRepresentation rep) {
2782 LABEL_BLOCK(no_change) { return Next::ReduceFloatUnary(input, kind, rep); }
2783 switch (kind) {
2784 case FloatUnaryOp::Kind::kRoundUp:
2785 case FloatUnaryOp::Kind::kRoundDown:
2786 case FloatUnaryOp::Kind::kRoundTiesEven:
2787 case FloatUnaryOp::Kind::kRoundToZero: {
2788 // TODO(14108): Implement for Float32.
2789 if (rep == FloatRepresentation::Float32()) {
2790 goto no_change;
2791 }
2792 DCHECK_EQ(rep, FloatRepresentation::Float64());
2793 V<Float64> input_f64 = V<Float64>::Cast(input);
2794 if (FloatUnaryOp::IsSupported(kind, rep)) {
2795 // If we have a fast machine operation for this, we can just keep it.
2796 goto no_change;
2797 }
2798 // Otherwise we have to lower it.
2799 V<Float64> two_52 = __ Float64Constant(4503599627370496.0E0);
2800 V<Float64> minus_two_52 = __ Float64Constant(-4503599627370496.0E0);
2801
2802 if (kind == FloatUnaryOp::Kind::kRoundUp) {
2803 // General case for ceil.
2804 //
2805 // if 0.0 < input then
2806 // if 2^52 <= input then
2807 // input
2808 // else
2809 // let temp1 = (2^52 + input) - 2^52 in
2810 // if temp1 < input then
2811 // temp1 + 1
2812 // else
2813 // temp1
2814 // else
2815 // if input == 0 then
2816 // input
2817 // else
2818 // if input <= -2^52 then
2819 // input
2820 // else
2821 // let temp1 = -0 - input in
2822 // let temp2 = (2^52 + temp1) - 2^52 in
2823 // if temp1 < temp2 then -0 - (temp2 - 1) else -0 - temp2
2824
2825 Label<Float64> done(this);
2826
2827 IF (LIKELY(__ Float64LessThan(0.0, input_f64))) {
2828 GOTO_IF(UNLIKELY(__ Float64LessThanOrEqual(two_52, input_f64)),
2829 done, input_f64);
2830 V<Float64> temp1 =
2831 __ Float64Sub(__ Float64Add(two_52, input_f64), two_52);
2832 GOTO_IF_NOT(__ Float64LessThan(temp1, input_f64), done, temp1);
2833 GOTO(done, __ Float64Add(temp1, 1.0));
2834 } ELSE IF (UNLIKELY(__ Float64Equal(input_f64, 0.0))) {
2835 GOTO(done, input_f64);
2836 } ELSE IF (UNLIKELY(
2837 __ Float64LessThanOrEqual(input_f64, minus_two_52))) {
2838 GOTO(done, input_f64);
2839 } ELSE {
2840 V<Float64> temp1 = __ Float64Sub(-0.0, input_f64);
2841 V<Float64> temp2 =
2842 __ Float64Sub(__ Float64Add(two_52, temp1), two_52);
2843 GOTO_IF_NOT(__ Float64LessThan(temp1, temp2), done,
2844 __ Float64Sub(-0.0, temp2));
2845 GOTO(done, __ Float64Sub(-0.0, __ Float64Sub(temp2, 1.0)));
2846 }
2847
2848 BIND(done, result);
2849 return result;
2850 } else if (kind == FloatUnaryOp::Kind::kRoundDown) {
2851 // General case for floor.
2852 //
2853 // if 0.0 < input then
2854 // if 2^52 <= input then
2855 // input
2856 // else
2857 // let temp1 = (2^52 + input) - 2^52 in
2858 // if input < temp1 then
2859 // temp1 - 1
2860 // else
2861 // temp1
2862 // else
2863 // if input == 0 then
2864 // input
2865 // else
2866 // if input <= -2^52 then
2867 // input
2868 // else
2869 // let temp1 = -0 - input in
2870 // let temp2 = (2^52 + temp1) - 2^52 in
2871 // if temp2 < temp1 then
2872 // -1 - temp2
2873 // else
2874 // -0 - temp2
2875
2876 Label<Float64> done(this);
2877
2878 IF (LIKELY(__ Float64LessThan(0.0, input_f64))) {
2879 GOTO_IF(UNLIKELY(__ Float64LessThanOrEqual(two_52, input_f64)),
2880 done, input_f64);
2881 V<Float64> temp1 =
2882 __ Float64Sub(__ Float64Add(two_52, input_f64), two_52);
2883 GOTO_IF_NOT(__ Float64LessThan(input_f64, temp1), done, temp1);
2884 GOTO(done, __ Float64Sub(temp1, 1.0));
2885 } ELSE IF (UNLIKELY(__ Float64Equal(input_f64, 0.0))) {
2886 GOTO(done, input_f64);
2887 } ELSE IF (UNLIKELY(
2888 __ Float64LessThanOrEqual(input_f64, minus_two_52))) {
2889 GOTO(done, input_f64);
2890 } ELSE {
2891 V<Float64> temp1 = __ Float64Sub(-0.0, input_f64);
2892 V<Float64> temp2 =
2893 __ Float64Sub(__ Float64Add(two_52, temp1), two_52);
2894 GOTO_IF_NOT(__ Float64LessThan(temp2, temp1), done,
2895 __ Float64Sub(-0.0, temp2));
2896 GOTO(done, __ Float64Sub(-1.0, temp2));
2897 }
2898
2899 BIND(done, result);
2900 return result;
2901 } else if (kind == FloatUnaryOp::Kind::kRoundTiesEven) {
2902 // Generate case for round ties to even:
2903 //
2904 // let value = floor(input) in
2905 // let temp1 = input - value in
2906 // if temp1 < 0.5 then
2907 // value
2908 // else if 0.5 < temp1 then
2909 // value + 1.0
2910 // else
2911 // let temp2 = value % 2.0 in
2912 // if temp2 == 0.0 then
2913 // value
2914 // else
2915 // value + 1.0
2916
2917 Label<Float64> done(this);
2918
2919 V<Float64> value = __ Float64RoundDown(input_f64);
2920 V<Float64> temp1 = __ Float64Sub(input_f64, value);
2921 GOTO_IF(__ Float64LessThan(temp1, 0.5), done, value);
2922 GOTO_IF(__ Float64LessThan(0.5, temp1), done,
2923 __ Float64Add(value, 1.0));
2924
2925 V<Float64> temp2 = __ Float64Mod(value, 2.0);
2926 GOTO_IF(__ Float64Equal(temp2, 0.0), done, value);
2927 GOTO(done, __ Float64Add(value, 1.0));
2928
2929 BIND(done, result);
2930 return result;
2931 } else if (kind == FloatUnaryOp::Kind::kRoundToZero) {
2932 // General case for trunc.
2933 //
2934 // if 0.0 < input then
2935 // if 2^52 <= input then
2936 // input
2937 // else
2938 // let temp1 = (2^52 + input) - 2^52 in
2939 // if input < temp1 then
2940 // temp1 - 1
2941 // else
2942 // temp1
2943 // else
2944 // if input == 0 then
2945 // input
2946 // if input <= -2^52 then
2947 // input
2948 // else
2949 // let temp1 = -0 - input in
2950 // let temp2 = (2^52 + temp1) - 2^52 in
2951 // if temp1 < temp2 then
2952 // -0 - (temp2 - 1)
2953 // else
2954 // -0 - temp2
2955
2956 Label<Float64> done(this);
2957
2958 IF (__ Float64LessThan(0.0, input_f64)) {
2959 GOTO_IF(UNLIKELY(__ Float64LessThanOrEqual(two_52, input_f64)),
2960 done, input_f64);
2961
2962 V<Float64> temp1 =
2963 __ Float64Sub(__ Float64Add(two_52, input_f64), two_52);
2964 GOTO_IF(__ Float64LessThan(input_f64, temp1), done,
2965 __ Float64Sub(temp1, 1.0));
2966 GOTO(done, temp1);
2967 } ELSE {
2968 GOTO_IF(UNLIKELY(__ Float64Equal(input_f64, 0.0)), done, input_f64);
2969 GOTO_IF(
2970 UNLIKELY(__ Float64LessThanOrEqual(input_f64, minus_two_52)),
2971 done, input_f64);
2972
2973 V<Float64> temp1 = __ Float64Sub(-0.0, input_f64);
2974 V<Float64> temp2 =
2975 __ Float64Sub(__ Float64Add(two_52, temp1), two_52);
2976
2977 IF (__ Float64LessThan(temp1, temp2)) {
2978 GOTO(done, __ Float64Sub(-0.0, __ Float64Sub(temp2, 1.0)));
2979 } ELSE {
2980 GOTO(done, __ Float64Sub(-0.0, temp2));
2981 }
2982 }
2983
2984 BIND(done, result);
2985 return result;
2986 }
2987 UNREACHABLE();
2988 }
2989 default:
2990 DCHECK(FloatUnaryOp::IsSupported(kind, rep));
2991 goto no_change;
2992 }
2993 UNREACHABLE();
2994 }

2999 V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(input);
3000 V<Word32> instance_type = __ LoadInstanceTypeField(map);

3008 // we recorded before.

3017 V<None> REDUCE(CheckEqualsInternalizedString)(V<Object> expected,
3018 V<Object> value,
3019 V<FrameState> frame_state) {
3020 Label<> done(this);
3021 // Check if {expected} and {value} are the same, which is the likely case.
3022 GOTO_IF(LIKELY(__ TaggedEqual(expected, value)), done);
3023
3024 // Now {value} could still be a non-internalized String that matches
3025 // {expected}.
3026 __ DeoptimizeIf(__ ObjectIsSmi(value), frame_state,
3027 DeoptimizeReason::kWrongName, FeedbackSource{});
3028 V<Map> value_map = __ LoadMapField(value);
3029 V<Word32> value_instance_type = __ LoadInstanceTypeField(value_map);
3030 V<Word32> value_representation =
3031 __ Word32BitwiseAnd(value_instance_type, kStringRepresentationMask);
3032 // ThinString
3033 IF (__ Word32Equal(value_representation, kThinStringTag)) {
3034 // The {value} is a ThinString, let's check the actual value.
3035 V<String> value_actual = __ template LoadField<String>(
3036 value, AccessBuilder::ForThinStringActual());
3037 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(__ TaggedEqual(expected, value_actual), frame_state,
3038 DeoptimizeReason::kWrongName, FeedbackSource{});
3039 } ELSE {
3040 // Check that the {value} is a non-internalized String, if it's anything
3041 // else it cannot match the recorded feedback {expected} anyways.
3042 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(
3043 __ Word32Equal(
3044 __ Word32BitwiseAnd(value_instance_type,
3045 kIsNotStringMask | kIsNotInternalizedMask),
3046 kStringTag | kNotInternalizedTag),
3047 frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongName, FeedbackSource{});
3048
3049 // Try to find the {value} in the string table.
3050 MachineSignature::Builder builder(__ graph_zone(), 1, 2);
3051 builder.AddReturn(MachineType::AnyTagged());
3052 builder.AddParam(MachineType::Pointer());
3053 builder.AddParam(MachineType::AnyTagged());
3054 OpIndex try_string_to_index_or_lookup_existing = __ ExternalConstant(
3055 ExternalReference::try_string_to_index_or_lookup_existing());
3056 OpIndex isolate_ptr =
3057 __ ExternalConstant(ExternalReference::isolate_address());
3058 V<String> value_internalized = V<String>::Cast(__ Call(
3059 try_string_to_index_or_lookup_existing, {isolate_ptr, value},
3060 TSCallDescriptor::Create(
3061 Linkage::GetSimplifiedCDescriptor(__ graph_zone(), builder.Get()),
3062 CanThrow::kNo, LazyDeoptOnThrow::kNo, __ graph_zone())));
3063
3064 // Now see if the results match.
3065 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(__ TaggedEqual(expected, value_internalized),
3066 frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongName,
3067 FeedbackSource{});
3068 }
3069
3070 GOTO(done);
3071
3072 BIND(done);
3073 return V<None>::Invalid();
3074 }

3097 V<Word32> REDUCE(Float64SameValue)(V<Float64> left, V<Float64> right) {
3098 Label<Word32> done(this);
3099
3100 IF (__ Float64Equal(left, right)) {
3101 // Even if the values are float64-equal, we still need to distinguish
3102 // zero and minus zero.
3103 V<Word32> left_hi = __ Float64ExtractHighWord32(left);
3104 V<Word32> right_hi = __ Float64ExtractHighWord32(right);
3105 GOTO(done, __ Word32Equal(left_hi, right_hi));
3106 } ELSE {
3107 // Return true iff both {lhs} and {rhs} are NaN.
3108 GOTO_IF(__ Float64Equal(left, left), done, 0);
3109 GOTO_IF(__ Float64Equal(right, right), done, 0);
3110 GOTO(done, 1);
3111 }
3112
3113 BIND(done, result);
3114 return result;

3144 V<Object> REDUCE(MaybeGrowFastElements)(V<Object> object, V<Object> elements,
3145 V<Word32> index,

3147 V<FrameState> frame_state,
3148 GrowFastElementsMode mode,
3149 const FeedbackSource& feedback) {
3150 Label<Object> done(this);
3151 // Check if we need to grow the {elements} backing store.
3152 GOTO_IF(LIKELY(__ Uint32LessThan(index, elements_length)), done, elements);

3154 V<Object> new_elements;

3160 case GrowFastElementsMode::kSmiOrObjectElements:
3161 new_elements = __ CallBuiltin_GrowFastSmiOrObjectElements(
3162 isolate_, object, __ TagSmi(index));
3163 break;

3167 __ DeoptimizeIf(__ ObjectIsSmi(new_elements), frame_state,
3168 DeoptimizeReason::kCouldNotGrowElements, feedback);

3175 V<None> REDUCE(TransitionElementsKind)(V<HeapObject> object,
3176 const ElementsTransition& transition) {
3177 V<Map> source_map = __ HeapConstant(transition.source().object());
3178 V<Map> target_map = __ HeapConstant(transition.target().object());
3179
3180 // Load the current map of {object}.
3181 V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(object);
3182
3183 // Check if {map} is the same as {source_map}.
3184 IF (UNLIKELY(__ TaggedEqual(map, source_map))) {
3185 switch (transition.mode()) {
3186 case ElementsTransition::kFastTransition:
3187 // In-place migration of {object}, just store the {target_map}.
3188 __ StoreField(object, AccessBuilder::ForMap(), target_map);
3189 break;
3190 case ElementsTransition::kSlowTransition:
3191 // Instance migration, call out to the runtime for {object}.
3192 __ CallRuntime_TransitionElementsKind(
3193 isolate_, __ NoContextConstant(), object, target_map);
3194 break;
3195 }
3196 }
3197
3198 return V<None>::Invalid();
3199 }
3200
3201 V<None> REDUCE(TransitionElementsKindOrCheckMap)(
3202 V<HeapObject> object, V<Map> map, V<FrameState> frame_state,
3203 const ElementsTransitionWithMultipleSources& transition) {
3204 Label<> done(this);
3205
3206 const MapRef target = transition.target();
3207 V<Map> target_map = __ HeapConstant(target.object());
3208
3209 IF (LIKELY(__ TaggedEqual(map, target_map))) {
3210 GOTO(done);
3211 }
3212
3213 const ZoneRefSet<Map>& transition_sources = transition.sources();
3214 for (const MapRef transition_source : transition_sources) {
3215 bool is_simple = IsSimpleMapChangeTransition(
3216 transition_source.elements_kind(), target.elements_kind());
3217
3218 IF (__ TaggedEqual(map, __ HeapConstant(transition_source.object()))) {
3219 if (is_simple) {
3220 // In-place migration of {object}, just store the {target_map}.
3221 __ StoreField(object, AccessBuilder::ForMap(), target_map);
3222 } else {
3223 // Instance migration, call out to the runtime for {object}.
3224 __ CallRuntime_TransitionElementsKind(
3225 isolate_, __ NoContextConstant(), object, target_map);
3226 }
3227 GOTO(done);
3228 }
3229 }
3230 // Successful transitions jumped to `done`. If we didn't jump, we know the
3231 // map is not the target map.
3232 __ Deoptimize(frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap,
3233 transition.feedback());
3234
3235 BIND(done);
3236
3237 // Inserting a AssumeMap so that subsequent optimizations know the map of
3238 // this object.
3239 ZoneRefSet<Map> maps({target}, __ graph_zone());
3240 __ AssumeMap(object, maps);
3241
3242 return V<None>::Invalid();
3243 }

3245 OpIndex REDUCE(FindOrderedHashEntry)(V<Object> data_structure, OpIndex key,
3246 FindOrderedHashEntryOp::Kind kind) {
3247 switch (kind) {
3248 case FindOrderedHashEntryOp::Kind::kFindOrderedHashMapEntry:
3249 return __ CallBuiltin_FindOrderedHashMapEntry(
3250 isolate_, __ NoContextConstant(), data_structure, key);
3251 case FindOrderedHashEntryOp::Kind::kFindOrderedHashMapEntryForInt32Key: {
3252 // Compute the integer hash code.
3253 V<WordPtr> hash = __ ChangeUint32ToUintPtr(ComputeUnseededHash(key));
3254
3255 V<WordPtr> number_of_buckets =
3256 __ ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(__ UntagSmi(__ template LoadField<Smi>(
3257 data_structure,
3258 AccessBuilder::ForOrderedHashMapOrSetNumberOfBuckets())));
3259 hash = __ WordPtrBitwiseAnd(hash, __ WordPtrSub(number_of_buckets, 1));
3260 V<WordPtr> first_entry = __ ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(__ UntagSmi(__ Load(
3261 data_structure,
3262 __ WordPtrAdd(__ WordPtrShiftLeft(hash, kTaggedSizeLog2),
3263 OrderedHashMap::HashTableStartOffset()),
3264 LoadOp::Kind::TaggedBase(), MemoryRepresentation::TaggedSigned())));
3265
3266 Label<WordPtr> done(this);
3267 LoopLabel<WordPtr> loop(this);
3268 GOTO(loop, first_entry);
3269
3270 BIND_LOOP(loop, entry) {
3271 GOTO_IF(__ WordPtrEqual(entry, OrderedHashMap::kNotFound), done,
3272 entry);
3273 V<WordPtr> candidate =
3274 __ WordPtrAdd(__ WordPtrMul(entry, OrderedHashMap::kEntrySize),
3275 number_of_buckets);
3276 V<Object> candidate_key = __ Load(
3277 data_structure,
3278 __ WordPtrAdd(__ WordPtrShiftLeft(candidate, kTaggedSizeLog2),
3279 OrderedHashMap::HashTableStartOffset()),
3280 LoadOp::Kind::TaggedBase(), MemoryRepresentation::AnyTagged());
3281
3282 IF (LIKELY(__ ObjectIsSmi(candidate_key))) {
3283 GOTO_IF(
3284 __ Word32Equal(__ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(candidate_key)), key),
3285 done, candidate);
3286 } ELSE IF (__ TaggedEqual(
3287 __ LoadMapField(candidate_key),
3288 __ HeapConstant(factory_->heap_number_map()))) {
3289 GOTO_IF(__ Float64Equal(__ LoadHeapNumberValue(
3290 V<HeapNumber>::Cast(candidate_key)),
3291 __ ChangeInt32ToFloat64(key)),
3292 done, candidate);
3293 }
3294
3295 V<WordPtr> next_entry = __ ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(__ UntagSmi(__ Load(
3296 data_structure,
3297 __ WordPtrAdd(__ WordPtrShiftLeft(candidate, kTaggedSizeLog2),
3298 (OrderedHashMap::HashTableStartOffset() +
3299 OrderedHashMap::kChainOffset * kTaggedSize)),
3300 LoadOp::Kind::TaggedBase(),
3301 MemoryRepresentation::TaggedSigned())));
3302 GOTO(loop, next_entry);
3303 }
3304
3305 BIND(done, result);
3306 return result;
3307 }
3308 case FindOrderedHashEntryOp::Kind::kFindOrderedHashSetEntry:
3309 return __ CallBuiltin_FindOrderedHashSetEntry(
3310 isolate_, __ NoContextConstant(), data_structure, key);
3311 }
3312 }

3314 // Loads a surrogate pair from {string} starting at {index} and returns the
3315 // result encode in {encoding}. Note that UTF32 encoding is identical to the
3316 // code point. If the string's {length} is already available, it can be
3317 // passed, otherwise it will be loaded when required.
3318 V<Word32> LoadSurrogatePairAt(V<String> string, OptionalV<WordPtr> length,
3319 V<WordPtr> index, UnicodeEncoding encoding) {
3320 Label<Word32> done(this);
3321
3322 V<Word32> first_code_unit = __ StringCharCodeAt(string, index);
3323 GOTO_IF_NOT(UNLIKELY(__ Word32Equal(
3324 __ Word32BitwiseAnd(first_code_unit, 0xFC00), 0xD800)),
3325 done, first_code_unit);
3326 if (!length.has_value()) {
3327 length = __ ChangeUint32ToUintPtr(__ template LoadField<Word32>(
3328 string, AccessBuilder::ForStringLength()));
3329 }
3330 V<WordPtr> next_index = __ WordPtrAdd(index, 1);
3331 GOTO_IF_NOT(__ IntPtrLessThan(next_index, length.value()), done,
3332 first_code_unit);
3333
3334 V<Word32> second_code_unit = __ StringCharCodeAt(string, next_index);
3335 GOTO_IF_NOT(
3336 __ Word32Equal(__ Word32BitwiseAnd(second_code_unit, 0xFC00), 0xDC00),
3337 done, first_code_unit);
3338
3339 switch (encoding) {
3340 case UnicodeEncoding::UTF16: {
3341// Need to swap the order for big-endian platforms
3342#if V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN
3343 V<Word32> value = __ Word32BitwiseOr(
3344 __ Word32ShiftLeft(first_code_unit, 16), second_code_unit);
3345#else
3346 V<Word32> value = __ Word32BitwiseOr(
3347 __ Word32ShiftLeft(second_code_unit, 16), first_code_unit);
3348#endif
3349 GOTO(done, value);
3350 break;
3351 }
3352 case UnicodeEncoding::UTF32: {
3353 const int32_t surrogate_offset = 0x10000 - (0xD800 << 10) - 0xDC00;
3354 V<Word32> value =
3355 __ Word32Add(__ Word32ShiftLeft(first_code_unit, 10),
3356 __ Word32Add(second_code_unit, surrogate_offset));
3357 GOTO(done, value);
3358 break;
3359 }
3360 }
3361
3362 BIND(done, result);
3363 return result;
3364 }

3366 V<String> StringFromSingleCharCode(V<Word32> code) {
3367 Label<String> done(this);
3368
3369 // Check if the {code} is a one byte character.
3370 IF (LIKELY(__ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(code, String::kMaxOneByteCharCode))) {
3371 // Load the isolate wide single character string table.
3372 V<FixedArray> table = __ SingleCharacterStringTableConstant();
3373
3374 // Compute the {table} index for {code}.
3375 V<WordPtr> index = __ ChangeUint32ToUintPtr(code);
3376
3377 // Load the string for the {code} from the single character string
3378 // table.
3379 V<String> entry = __ LoadElement(
3380 table, AccessBuilderTS::ForFixedArrayElement<String>(), index);
3381
3382 // Use the {entry} from the {table}.
3383 GOTO(done, entry);
3384 } ELSE {
3385 Uninitialized<SeqTwoByteString> string =
3386 AllocateSeqTwoByteString(1, AllocationType::kYoung);
3387 __ InitializeElement(
3388 string, AccessBuilderTS::ForSeqTwoByteStringCharacter(), 0, code);
3389 GOTO(done, __ FinishInitialization(std::move(string)));
3390 }
3391
3392 BIND(done, result);
3393 return result;
3394 }
3395
3396 V<String> StringFromSingleCodePoint(V<Word32> codepoint,
3397 UnicodeEncoding encoding) {
3398 Label<String> done(this);
3399 // Check if the input is a single code unit.
3400 GOTO_IF(LIKELY(__ Uint32LessThan(codepoint, 0x10000)), done,
3401 StringFromSingleCharCode(codepoint));
3402
3403 V<Word32> code;
3404 switch (encoding) {
3405 case UnicodeEncoding::UTF16:
3406 code = codepoint;
3407 break;
3408 case UnicodeEncoding::UTF32: {
3409 // Convert UTF32 to UTF16 code units and store as a 32 bit word.
3410 V<Word32> lead_offset = __ Word32Constant(0xD800 - (0x10000 >> 10));
3411
3412 // lead = (codepoint >> 10) + LEAD_OFFSET
3413 V<Word32> lead = __ Word32Add(__ Word32ShiftRightLogical(codepoint, 10),
3414 lead_offset);
3415
3416 // trail = (codepoint & 0x3FF) + 0xDC00
3417 V<Word32> trail =
3418 __ Word32Add(__ Word32BitwiseAnd(codepoint, 0x3FF), 0xDC00);
3419
3420 // codepoint = (trail << 16) | lead
3421#if V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN
3422 code = __ Word32BitwiseOr(__ Word32ShiftLeft(lead, 16), trail);
3423#else
3424 code = __ Word32BitwiseOr(__ Word32ShiftLeft(trail, 16), lead);
3425#endif
3426 break;
3427 }
3428 }
3429
3430 Uninitialized<SeqTwoByteString> string =
3431 AllocateSeqTwoByteString(2, AllocationType::kYoung);
3432 // Write the code as a single 32-bit value by adapting the elements
3433 // access to SeqTwoByteString characters.
3434 auto access = AccessBuilderTS::ForSeqTwoByteStringCharacter();
3435 access.machine_type = MachineType::Uint32();
3436 __ InitializeElement(string, access, 0, code);
3437 GOTO(done, __ FinishInitialization(std::move(string)));
3438
3439 BIND(done, result);
3440 return result;
3441 }
3442
3443 Uninitialized<SeqTwoByteString> AllocateSeqTwoByteString(
3444 uint32_t length, AllocationType type) {
3445 __ CodeComment("AllocateSeqTwoByteString");
3446 DCHECK_GT(length, 0);
3447 // Allocate a new string object.
3448 Uninitialized<SeqTwoByteString> string =
3449 __ template Allocate<SeqTwoByteString>(
3450 SeqTwoByteString::SizeFor(length), type);
3451 // Set padding to 0.
3452 __ Initialize(string, __ IntPtrConstant(0),
3453 MemoryRepresentation::TaggedSigned(),
3454 WriteBarrierKind::kNoWriteBarrier,
3455 SeqTwoByteString::SizeFor(length) - kObjectAlignment);
3456 // Initialize remaining fields.
3457 __ InitializeField(string, AccessBuilderTS::ForMap(),
3458 __ SeqTwoByteStringMapConstant());
3459 __ InitializeField(string, AccessBuilderTS::ForStringLength(), length);
3460 __ InitializeField(string, AccessBuilderTS::ForNameRawHashField(),
3461 Name::kEmptyHashField);
3462 // Do not finish allocation here, because the caller has to initialize
3463 // characters.
3464 return string;
3465 }

3483 V<Word32> BuildUint32Mod(V<Word32> left, V<Word32> right) {
3484 Label<Word32> done(this);
3485
3486 // Compute the mask for the {rhs}.
3487 V<Word32> msk = __ Word32Sub(right, 1);
3488
3489 // Check if the {rhs} is a power of two.
3490 IF (__ Word32Equal(__ Word32BitwiseAnd(right, msk), 0)) {
3491 // The {rhs} is a power of two, just do a fast bit masking.
3492 GOTO(done, __ Word32BitwiseAnd(left, msk));
3493 } ELSE {
3494 // The {rhs} is not a power of two, do a generic Uint32Mod.
3495 GOTO(done, __ Uint32Mod(left, right));
3496 }
3497
3498 BIND(done, result);
3499 return result;
3500 }

3502 // Pass {bitfield} = {digit} = OpIndex::Invalid() to construct the canonical
3503 // 0n BigInt.
3504 V<BigInt> AllocateBigInt(V<Word32> bitfield, V<Word64> digit) {
3505 if (Asm().generating_unreachable_operations()) return V<BigInt>::Invalid();
3506
3507 DCHECK(Is64());
3508 DCHECK_EQ(bitfield.valid(), digit.valid());
3509 static constexpr auto zero_bitfield =
3510 BigInt::SignBits::update(BigInt::LengthBits::encode(0), false);
3511
3512 V<Map> map = __ HeapConstant(factory_->bigint_map());
3513 auto bigint = __ template Allocate<FreshlyAllocatedBigInt>(
3514 __ IntPtrConstant(BigInt::SizeFor(digit.valid() ? 1 : 0)),
3515 AllocationType::kYoung);
3516 __ InitializeField(bigint, AccessBuilder::ForMap(), map);
3517 __ InitializeField(
3518 bigint, AccessBuilder::ForBigIntBitfield(),
3519 bitfield.valid() ? bitfield : __ Word32Constant(zero_bitfield));
3520
3521 // BigInts have no padding on 64 bit architectures with pointer compression.
3522#ifdef BIGINT_NEEDS_PADDING
3523 __ InitializeField(bigint, AccessBuilder::ForBigIntOptionalPadding(),
3524 __ Word32Constant(0));
3525#endif
3526 if (digit.valid()) {
3527 __ InitializeField(
3528 bigint, AccessBuilder::ForBigIntLeastSignificantDigit64(), digit);
3529 }
3530 return V<BigInt>::Cast(__ FinishInitialization(std::move(bigint)));
3531 }
3532
3533 void TagSmiOrOverflow(V<Word32> input, Label<>* overflow,
3534 Label<Number>* done) {
3535 DCHECK(SmiValuesAre31Bits());
3536
3537 // Check for overflow at the same time that we are smi tagging.
3538 // Since smi tagging shifts left by one, it's the same as adding value
3539 // twice.
3540 V<Tuple<Word32, Word32>> add = __ Int32AddCheckOverflow(input, input);
3541 V<Word32> check = __ template Projection<1>(add);
3542 GOTO_IF(UNLIKELY(check), *overflow);
3543 GOTO(*done, __ BitcastWord32ToSmi(__ template Projection<0>(add)));
3544 }
3545
3546 // `IsNonZero` converts any non-0 value into 1.
3547 V<Word32> IsNonZero(V<Word32> value) {
3548 return __ Word32Equal(__ Word32Equal(value, 0), 0);
3549 }
3550
3551 V<HeapNumber> AllocateHeapNumber(V<Float64> value) {
3552 return __ AllocateHeapNumberWithValue(value, factory_);
3553 }
3554
3555 V<Float64> ConvertHeapObjectToFloat64OrDeopt(
3556 V<Object> heap_object, V<FrameState> frame_state,
3557 ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::JSPrimitiveKind input_kind,
3558 const FeedbackSource& feedback) {
3559 V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(heap_object);
3560 switch (input_kind) {
3561 case ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kSmi:
3562 case ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::JSPrimitiveKind::
3563 kNumberOrString:
3564 UNREACHABLE();
3565 case ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kNumber: {
3566 V<Word32> is_number =
3567 __ TaggedEqual(map, __ HeapConstant(factory_->heap_number_map()));
3568 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(is_number, frame_state,
3569 DeoptimizeReason::kNotAHeapNumber, feedback);
3570 break;
3571 }
3572 case ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::JSPrimitiveKind::
3573 kNumberOrBoolean: {
3574#if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
3575 // TODO(leszeks): Consider checking the boolean oddballs by value,
3576 // before loading the map.
3577 static_assert(StaticReadOnlyRoot::kBooleanMap + Map::kSize ==
3578 StaticReadOnlyRoot::kHeapNumberMap);
3579 V<Word32> map_int32 =
3580 __ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(__ BitcastHeapObjectToWordPtr(map));
3581 V<Word32> is_in_range = __ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(
3582 __ Word32Sub(map_int32,
3583 __ Word32Constant(StaticReadOnlyRoot::kBooleanMap)),
3584 __ Word32Constant(StaticReadOnlyRoot::kHeapNumberMap -
3585 StaticReadOnlyRoot::kBooleanMap));
3586 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(is_in_range, frame_state,
3587 DeoptimizeReason::kNotANumberOrBoolean, feedback);
3588#else
3589 IF_NOT (__ TaggedEqual(map,
3590 __ HeapConstant(factory_->heap_number_map()))) {
3591 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(
3592 __ TaggedEqual(map, __ HeapConstant(factory_->boolean_map())),
3593 frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kNotANumberOrBoolean, feedback);
3594 }
3595#endif
3596
3597 break;
3598 }
3599 case ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::JSPrimitiveKind::
3600 kNumberOrOddball: {
3601#if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
3602 constexpr auto kNumberOrOddballRange =
3603 InstanceTypeChecker::UniqueMapRangeOfInstanceTypeRange(
3604 HEAP_NUMBER_TYPE, ODDBALL_TYPE)
3605 .value();
3606 V<Word32> map_int32 =
3607 __ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(__ BitcastHeapObjectToWordPtr(map));
3608 V<Word32> is_in_range = __ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(
3609 __ Word32Sub(map_int32,
3610 __ Word32Constant(kNumberOrOddballRange.first)),
3611 __ Word32Constant(kNumberOrOddballRange.second -
3612 kNumberOrOddballRange.first));
3613 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(is_in_range, frame_state,
3614 DeoptimizeReason::kNotANumberOrOddball, feedback);
3615#else
3616 IF_NOT (__ TaggedEqual(map,
3617 __ HeapConstant(factory_->heap_number_map()))) {
3618 // For oddballs also contain the numeric value, let us just check that
3619 // we have an oddball here.
3620 V<Word32> instance_type = __ LoadInstanceTypeField(map);
3621 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(__ Word32Equal(instance_type, ODDBALL_TYPE),
3622 frame_state,
3623 DeoptimizeReason::kNotANumberOrOddball, feedback);
3624 }
3625#endif
3626
3627 break;
3628 }
3629 }
3630 return __ template LoadField<Float64>(
3631 heap_object, AccessBuilder::ForHeapNumberOrOddballOrHoleValue());
3632 }
3633
3634 V<Word32> LoadFromSeqString(V<Object> receiver, V<WordPtr> position,
3635 V<Word32> onebyte) {
3636 Label<Word32> done(this);
3637
3638 IF (onebyte) {
3639 GOTO(done, __ template LoadNonArrayBufferElement<Word32>(
3640 receiver, AccessBuilder::ForSeqOneByteStringCharacter(),
3641 position));
3642 } ELSE {
3643 GOTO(done, __ template LoadNonArrayBufferElement<Word32>(
3644 receiver, AccessBuilder::ForSeqTwoByteStringCharacter(),
3645 position));
3646 }
3647
3648 BIND(done, result);
3649 return result;
3650 }

3652 void MigrateInstanceOrDeopt(V<HeapObject> heap_object, V<Map> heap_object_map,
3653 V<FrameState> frame_state,
3654 const FeedbackSource& feedback) {
3655 // If {heap_object_map} is not deprecated, the migration attempt does not
3656 // make sense.
3657 V<Word32> bitfield3 = __ template LoadField<Word32>(
3658 heap_object_map, AccessBuilder::ForMapBitField3());
3659 V<Word32> deprecated =
3660 __ Word32BitwiseAnd(bitfield3, Map::Bits3::IsDeprecatedBit::kMask);
3661 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(deprecated, frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap,
3662 feedback);
3663 V<Object> result = __ CallRuntime_TryMigrateInstance(
3664 isolate_, __ NoContextConstant(), heap_object);
3665 // TryMigrateInstance returns a Smi value to signal failure.
3666 __ DeoptimizeIf(__ ObjectIsSmi(result), frame_state,
3667 DeoptimizeReason::kInstanceMigrationFailed, feedback);
3668 }

3670 void TryMigrateInstanceAndMarkMapAsMigrationTarget(

3675 V<Word32> bitfield3 = __ template LoadField<Word32>(
3676 heap_object_map, AccessBuilder::ForMapBitField3());
3677 V<Word32> deprecated =
3678 __ Word32BitwiseAnd(bitfield3, Map::Bits3::IsDeprecatedBit::kMask);
3679 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(deprecated, frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap,
3680 feedback);
3681 __ CallRuntime_TryMigrateInstanceAndMarkMapAsMigrationTarget(
3682 isolate_, __ NoContextConstant(), heap_object);
3683 }

3685 // TODO(nicohartmann@): Might use the CallBuiltinDescriptors here.
3686 OpIndex CallBuiltinForBigIntOp(Builtin builtin,
3687 std::initializer_list<OpIndex> arguments) {
3688 DCHECK_IMPLIES(builtin == Builtin::kBigIntUnaryMinus,
3689 arguments.size() == 1);
3690 DCHECK_IMPLIES(builtin != Builtin::kBigIntUnaryMinus,
3691 arguments.size() == 2);
3692 base::SmallVector<OpIndex, 4> args(arguments);
3693 args.push_back(__ NoContextConstant());
3694
3695 Callable callable = Builtins::CallableFor(isolate_, builtin);
3696 auto descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
3697 __ graph_zone(), callable.descriptor(),
3698 callable.descriptor().GetStackParameterCount(),
3699 CallDescriptor::kNoFlags, Operator::kFoldable | Operator::kNoThrow);
3700 auto ts_descriptor = TSCallDescriptor::Create(
3701 descriptor, CanThrow::kNo, LazyDeoptOnThrow::kNo, __ graph_zone());
3702 return __ Call(__ HeapConstant(callable.code()), V<FrameState>::Invalid(),
3703 base::VectorOf(args), ts_descriptor);
3704 }

3714 case BigIntBinopOp::Kind::kDiv:

3716 case BigIntBinopOp::Kind::kMod:

3718 case BigIntBinopOp::Kind::kBitwiseAnd:
3719 return Builtin::kBigIntBitwiseAndNoThrow;
3720 case BigIntBinopOp::Kind::kBitwiseOr:
3721 return Builtin::kBigIntBitwiseOrNoThrow;
3722 case BigIntBinopOp::Kind::kBitwiseXor:
3723 return Builtin::kBigIntBitwiseXorNoThrow;
3724 case BigIntBinopOp::Kind::kShiftLeft:

3730
3731 V<WordPtr> BuildTypedArrayDataPointer(V<Object> base, V<WordPtr> external) {
3732 if (__ matcher().MatchZero(base)) return external;
3733 V<WordPtr> untagged_base = __ BitcastTaggedToWordPtr(base);
3734 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
3735 // Zero-extend Tagged_t to UintPtr according to current compression
3736 // scheme so that the addition with |external_pointer| (which already
3737 // contains compensated offset value) will decompress the tagged value.
3738 // See JSTypedArray::ExternalPointerCompensationForOnHeapArray() for
3739 // details.
3740 untagged_base =
3741 __ ChangeUint32ToUintPtr(__ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(untagged_base));
3742 }
3743 return __ WordPtrAdd(untagged_base, external);
3744 }
3745
3746 V<Word32> ComputeUnseededHash(V<Word32> value) {
3747 // See v8::internal::ComputeUnseededHash()
3748 value = __ Word32Add(__ Word32BitwiseXor(value, 0xFFFFFFFF),
3749 __ Word32ShiftLeft(value, 15));
3750 value = __ Word32BitwiseXor(value, __ Word32ShiftRightLogical(value, 12));
3751 value = __ Word32Add(value, __ Word32ShiftLeft(value, 2));
3752 value = __ Word32BitwiseXor(value, __ Word32ShiftRightLogical(value, 4));
3753 value = __ Word32Mul(value, 2057);
3754 value = __ Word32BitwiseXor(value, __ Word32ShiftRightLogical(value, 16));
3755 value = __ Word32BitwiseAnd(value, 0x3FFFFFFF);
3756 return value;
3757 }
3758
3759 void TransitionElementsTo(V<JSArray> array, ElementsKind from,
3760 ElementsKind to, Handle<Map> target_map) {
3761 DCHECK(IsMoreGeneralElementsKindTransition(from, to));
3762 DCHECK(to == HOLEY_ELEMENTS || to == HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS);
3763
3764 if (IsSimpleMapChangeTransition(from, to)) {
3765 __ StoreField(array, AccessBuilder::ForMap(),
3766 __ HeapConstant(target_map));
3767 } else {
3768 // Instance migration, call out to the runtime for {array}.
3769 __ CallRuntime_TransitionElementsKind(isolate_, __ NoContextConstant(),
3770 array, __ HeapConstant(target_map));
3771 }
3772 }
3773
3774 V<Word32> CompareMapAgainstMultipleMaps(V<Map> heap_object_map,
3775 const ZoneRefSet<Map>& maps) {
3776 if (maps.is_empty()) {
3777 return __ Word32Constant(0);
3778 }
3779 V<Word32> result;
3780 for (size_t i = 0; i < maps.size(); ++i) {
3781 V<Map> map = __ HeapConstant(maps[i].object());
3782 if (i == 0) {
3783 result = __ TaggedEqual(heap_object_map, map);
3784 } else {
3785 result =
3786 __ Word32BitwiseOr(result, __ TaggedEqual(heap_object_map, map));
3787 }
3788 }
3789 return result;
3790 }
3791
3792 bool DependOnNoUndetectableObjectsProtector() {
3793 if (!undetectable_objects_protector_) {
3794 UnparkedScopeIfNeeded unpark(broker_);
3795 undetectable_objects_protector_ =
3796 broker_->dependencies()->DependOnNoUndetectableObjectsProtector();
3797 }
3798 return *undetectable_objects_protector_;
3799 }
3800
3801 Isolate* isolate_ = __ data() -> isolate();
3802 Factory* factory_ = isolate_ ? isolate_->factory() : nullptr;
3803 JSHeapBroker* broker_ = __ data() -> broker();
3804 std::optional<bool> undetectable_objects_protector_ = {};
3805};
